  nickname: job
  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 255596ce6b91ac640b392e20dd4f8a9e, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Job\u2019s Character and Wealth"
      title: "Job\u2019s Character and Wealth"
      number: 1
      content: '    There was a man in the land of Uz whose name was Job; and that
        man was blameless and upright, and one who feared God [with reverence] and
        abstained from and turned away from evil [because he honored God]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Seven sons and three daughters were born to him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'He also possessed 7,000 sheep, 3,000 camels, 500 yoke (pairs) of
        oxen, 500 female donkeys, and a very great number of servants, so that this
        man was the greatest [and wealthiest and most respected] of all the men of
        the east (northern Arabia). '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'His sons used to go [in turn] and feast in the house of each one
        on his day, and they would send word and invite their three sisters to eat
        and drink with them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "When the days of their feasting were over, Job would send [for them]
        and consecrate them, rising early in the morning and offering burnt offerings
        according to the number of them all; for Job said, \u201CIt may be that my
        sons have sinned and cursed God in their hearts.\u201D Job did this at all
        [such] times.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Now there was a day when the sons of God (angels) came to present
        themselves before the Lord, and Satan (adversary, accuser) also came among
        them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "The Lord said to Satan, \u201CFrom where have you come?\u201D Then
        Satan answered the Lord, \u201CFrom roaming around on the earth and from
        walking around on it.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "The Lord said to Satan, \u201CHave you considered and reflected on
        My servant Job? For there is none like him on the earth, a blameless and
        upright man, one who fears God [with reverence] and abstains from and turns
        away from evil [because he honors God].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then Satan answered the Lord, \u201CDoes Job fear God for nothing? "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Have You not put a hedge [of protection] around him and his house
        and all that he has, on every side? You have blessed the work of his hands
        [and conferred prosperity and happiness upon him], and his possessions have
        increased in the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "But put forth Your hand now and touch (destroy) all that he has,
        and he will surely curse You to Your face.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: Satan Allowed to Test Job'
      title: Satan Allowed to Test Job
      number: 12
      content: "Then the Lord said to Satan, \u201CBehold, all that Job has is in
        your power, only do not put your hand on the man himself.\u201D So Satan
        departed from the presence of the Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Now there was a day when Job\u2019s sons and daughters were eating
        and drinking wine in their oldest brother\u2019s house, "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "and a messenger came to Job and said, \u201CThe oxen were plowing
        and the donkeys were feeding beside them, "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "and the Sabeans attacked and swooped down on them and took away the
        animals. They also killed the servants with the edge of the sword, and I
        alone have escaped to tell you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "While he was still speaking, another [messenger] also came and said,
        \u201CThe fire of God (lightning) has fallen from the heavens and has burned
        up the sheep and the servants and consumed them, and I alone have escaped
        to tell you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "While he was still speaking, another [messenger] also came and said,
        \u201CThe Chaldeans formed three bands and made a raid on the camels and
        have taken them away and have killed the servants with the edge of the sword,
        and I alone have escaped to tell you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "While he was still speaking, another [messenger] also came and said,
        \u201CYour sons and your daughters were eating and drinking wine in their
        oldest brother\u2019s house, "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "and suddenly, a great wind came from across the desert, and struck
        the four corners of the house, and it fell on the young people and they died,
        and I alone have escaped to tell you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Then Job got up and tore his robe and shaved his head [in mourning
        for the children], and he fell to the ground and worshiped [God]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "He said,\u201CNaked (without possessions) I came [into this world]
        from my mother\u2019s womb,And naked I will return there.The Lord gave and
        the Lord has taken away;Blessed be the name of the Lord.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: Through all this Job did not sin nor did he blame God.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Job Loses His Health'
      title: Job Loses His Health
      number: 1
      content: '  Again there was a day when the sons of God (angels) came to present
        themselves before the Lord, and Satan (adversary, accuser) also came among
        them to present himself before the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "The Lord said to Satan, \u201CFrom where have you come?\u201D Then
        Satan answered the Lord, \u201CFrom roaming around on the earth and from
        walking around on it.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "The Lord said to Satan, \u201CHave you considered and reflected on
        My servant Job? For there is none like him on the earth, a blameless and
        upright man, one who fears God [with reverence] and abstains from and turns
        away from evil [because he honors God]. And still he maintains and holds
        tightly to his integrity, although you incited Me against him to destroy
        him without cause.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Satan answered the Lord, \u201CSkin for skin! Yes, a man will give
        all he has for his life. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "But put forth Your hand now, and touch his bone and his flesh [and
        severely afflict him]; and he will curse You to Your face.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So the Lord said to Satan, \u201CBehold, he is in your hand, only
        spare his life.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'So Satan departed from the presence of the Lord and struck Job with
        loathsome boils and agonizingly painful sores from the sole of his foot to
        the crown of his head. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And Job took a piece of broken pottery with which to scrape himself,
        and he sat [down] among the ashes (rubbish heaps).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then his wife said to him, \u201CDo you still cling to your integrity
        [and your faith and trust in God, without blaming Him]? Curse God and die!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "But he said to her, \u201CYou speak as one of the [spiritually] foolish
        women speaks [ignorant and oblivious to God\u2019s will]. Shall we indeed
        accept [only] good from God and not [also] accept adversity and disaster?\u201D
        In [spite of] all this Job did not sin with [words from] his lips.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Now when Job\u2019s three friends heard of all this adversity that
        had come upon him, each one came from his own place, Eliphaz the Temanite,
        Bildad the Shuhite, and Zophar the Naamathite; for they had made an appointment
        together to come to sympathize with him and to comfort him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'When they looked from a distance and did not recognize him [because
        of his disfigurement], they raised their voices and wept; and each one tore
        his robe [in grief] and they threw dust over their heads toward the sky [in
        sorrow]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: So they sat down on the ground with Job for seven days and seven nights
        and no one spoke a word to him, for they saw that his pain was very great.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Job\u2019s Lament"
      title: "Job\u2019s Lament"
      number: 1
      content: '  After this, Job opened his mouth and cursed the day of his birth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And Job said,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CLet the day on which I was born perish,And the night which
        announced: \u2018There is a man-child conceived.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'May that day be darkness;Let God above not care about it,Nor light
        shine on it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Let darkness and gloom claim it for their own;Let a cloud settle
        upon it;Let all that blackens the day terrify it (the day that I was born).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'As for that night, let darkness seize it;Let it not rejoice among
        the days of the year;Let it not be counted in the number of the months.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Behold, let that night be barren [and empty];Let no joyful voice
        enter it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Let those curse it who curse the day,Who are skilled in rousing up
        Leviathan.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Let the stars of its early dawn be dark;Let the morning wait in vain
        for the light,Let it not see the eyelids of morning (the day\u2019s dawning),  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Because it did not shut the doors of my mother\u2019s womb,Nor hide
        trouble from my eyes.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CWhy did I not die at birth,Come forth from the womb and expire?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Why did the knees receive me?And why the breasts, that I would nurse?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'For now I would have lain down and been quiet;I would have slept
        then, I would have been at rest [in death],  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'With kings and counselors of the earth,Who built up [now desolate]
        ruins for themselves;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Or with princes who had gold,Who filled their houses with silver.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Or like a miscarriage which is hidden and put away, I would not exist,Like
        infants who never saw light.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'There [in death] the wicked cease from raging,And there the weary
        are at rest.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "There the prisoners rest together;They do not hear the taskmaster\u2019s
        voice.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'The small and the great are there,And the servant is free from his
        master.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CWhy is the light given to him who is in misery,And life to
        the bitter in soul,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Who wait for death, but it does not come,And dig (search) for death
        more [diligently] than for hidden treasures,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Who rejoice exceedingly,And rejoice when they find the grave?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: '  Why is the light of day given to a man whose way is hidden,And
        whom God has hedged in?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'For my groaning comes at the sight of my food,And my cries [of despair]
        are poured out like water.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'For the thing which I greatly fear comes upon me,And that of which
        I am afraid has come upon me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "I am not at ease, nor am I quiet,And I am not at rest, and yet trouble
        still comes [upon me].\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Eliphaz: Innocent Do Not Suffer'
      title: 'Eliphaz: Innocent Do Not Suffer'
      number: 1
      content: '  Then Eliphaz the Temanite answered and said,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CIf we dare to converse with you, will you be impatient [or
        offended]?But who can restrain himself from speaking?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Behold, you have admonished and instructed many,And you have strengthened
        weak hands.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Your words have helped the one who was stumbling to stand,And you
        have strengthened feeble knees.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'But now adversity comes upon you, and you are impatient and intolerant;It
        touches you, and you are horrified.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Is not your fear of God your confidence,And [is not] the integrity
        and uprightness of your ways your hope?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CRemember now, who, being innocent, ever perished?Or where [and
        in what circumstances] were those upright and in right standing with God
        destroyed?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'As I have seen, those who plow wickednessAnd those who sow trouble
        and harm harvest it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'By the breath of God they perish,And by the blast of His anger they
        are consumed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The roaring of the lion and the voice of the fierce lion,And the
        teeth of the young lions are broken.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'The lion perishes for lack of prey,And the cubs of the lioness are
        scattered.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CNow a word was secretly brought to me,And my ear received a
        whisper of it.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Amid disquieting thoughts from the visions of the night,When deep
        sleep falls on men,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Dread and trembling came upon me,Which made all my bones shake.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Then a spirit passed before my face;The hair on my skin stood on
        end!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'The spirit stood still, but I could not discern its appearance;A
        form was before my eyes;  There was silence, and then I heard a voice, saying:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u2018Can [mortal] man be just before God or be more righteous than
        He?Can a man be pure before his Maker or be more cleansed than He?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'God puts no trust or confidence, even in His [heavenly] servants,And
        He charges His angels with error.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'How much more [will He blame and charge] those who dwell in houses
        (bodies) of clay,Whose foundations are in the dust,Who are crushed like a
        moth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Between morning and evening they are broken in pieces and destroyed;Unobserved
        and unnoticed, they perish forever.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Is not their tent-cord drawn up within them [so that the tent collapses]?Do
        they not die, and yet without [acquiring] wisdom?\u2019"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: God Is Just'
      title: God Is Just
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CCall now\u2014is there anyone who will answer you?And to
        which of the holy ones (angels) will you turn?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'For anger slays the foolish man,And jealousy kills the simple (naive).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'I have seen the foolish taking root [and outwardly prospering],But
        I cursed his dwelling immediately [for his destruction was certain].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "His children are far from safety [and included in their father\u2019s
        ruin],They are oppressed and crushed in the [court of justice in the city\u2019s]
        gate,And there is no one to rescue them.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The hungry devour his harvestAnd take it even [when it grows] among
        the thorns;The trap opens for [his] wealth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'For affliction does not come forth from the dust,Nor does trouble
        spring forth from the ground.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'For man is born for trouble,[As naturally] as sparks fly upward.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CAs for me, I would seek God and inquire of Him,And I would
        commit my cause to God;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Who does great and unsearchable things,Marvelous things without number.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'He gives rain upon the earthAnd sends waters upon the fields,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'So that He sets on high those who are lowly,And He lifts to safety
        those who mourn.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'He frustrates the devices and schemes of the crafty,So that their
        hands cannot attain success or achieve anything of [lasting] worth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'He catches the [so-called] wise in their own shrewdness,And the advice
        of the devious is quickly thwarted.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'In the daytime they meet in darkness,And at noon they grope as in
        the night.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'But God saves [the innocent] from the sword of the mouth of the devious,And
        the poor from the hand of the mighty.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'So the helpless have hope,And injustice shuts its mouth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CBehold, how happy and fortunate is the man whom God reproves,So
        do not despise or reject the discipline of the Almighty [subjecting you to
        trial and suffering].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'For He inflicts pain, but He binds up and gives relief;He wounds,
        but His hands also heal.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'He will rescue you from six troubles;Even in seven, evil will not
        touch you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'In famine He will redeem you from death,And in war from the power
        of the sword.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'You will be hidden from the scourge of the tongue,And you will not
        be afraid of destruction when it comes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'You will laugh at violence and famine,And you will not be afraid
        of the wild beasts of the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'For you will be in harmony with the stones of the field,And the beasts
        of the field will be at peace with you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'You will know also that your tent is secure and at peace,And you
        will visit your dwelling and fear no loss [nor find anything amiss].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'You will know also that your descendants will be many,And your offspring
        as the grass of the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'You will come to your grave in old age,Like the stacking of grain
        [on the threshing floor] in its season.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Behold this; we have investigated it, and it is true.Hear and heed
        it, and know for yourself [for your own good].\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Job\u2019s Friends Are No Help"
      title: "Job\u2019s Friends Are No Help"
      number: 1
      content: '  Then Job answered and said,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201COh, that my grief could actually be weighedAnd placed in the
        balances together with my tragedy [to see if my grief is the grief of a coward]!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For now it would be heavier than the sand of the sea;Therefore my
        words have been incoherent,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Because the arrows of the Almighty are within me,My spirit drinks
        their poison;The terrors of God are arrayed against me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Does the wild donkey bray when he has grass?Or does the ox low over
        his fodder?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Can something that has no taste to it be eaten without salt?Or is
        there any flavor in the white of an egg?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'My soul refuses to touch them;Such things are like loathsome food
        to me [sickening and repugnant].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201COh that my request would come to pass,And that God would grant
        me the thing that I long for!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'I wish that it would please God to crush me,That He would let loose
        His hand and cut me off.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Then I would still have consolation,And I would jump for joy amid
        unsparing pain,That I have not denied or hidden the words of the Holy One.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'What strength do I have left, that I should wait [and hope]?And what
        is ahead of me, that I should be patient and endure?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Is my strength and endurance that of stones,Or is my flesh made of
        bronze?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Is it that I have no help within myself,And that success and wisdom
        have been driven from me?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CFor the despairing man there should be kindness from his friend;So
        that he does not abandon (turn away from) the fear of the Almighty.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'My brothers have acted deceitfully like a brook,Like the torrents
        of brooks that vanish,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Which are dull and dirty because of ice,And into which the snow melts
        and hides itself;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'When it is warm, they are silent and cease to flow;When it is hot,
        they vanish from their place.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'The paths of their course wind along,They go up into nothing and
        perish.[Your counsel is as helpful to me as a dry streambed in the heat of
        summer.]  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'The caravans of Tema looked [for water],The caravans of Sheba waited
        for them [in vain].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'They were put to shame and disappointed because they had trusted
        [that they would find water];They came there and were ashamed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Indeed, you have now become like a dried-up stream,You see a terror
        [believing me to be a victim of the wrath of God] and are afraid [to be compassionate].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Did I ever say, \u2018Give me something,\u2019Or, \u2018Pay a bribe
        for me from your wealth,\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Or, \u2018Rescue me from the adversary\u2019s hand,\u2019Or, \u2018Redeem
        me from the hand of the tyrants\u2019?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u201CTeach me, and I will be silent;And show me how I have erred.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'How painful are words of honesty.But what does your argument prove?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Do you intend to reprove my words [with a convincing argument],When
        the words of one in despair belong to the wind [and go ignored]?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'You would cast lots (gamble) over the fatherlessAnd bargain away
        your friend.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Now please look at me,And see if I lie to your face [for you know
        that I would not].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Turn away [from your suspicion], let there be no injustice;Turn away,
        my righteousness and vindication is still in it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: Is there injustice or malice on my tongue?Can my palate not discern
        what is destructive?
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Job\u2019s Life Seems Futile"
      title: "Job\u2019s Life Seems Futile"
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CIs not man forced to labor on earth?And are not his days
        like the days of a hired man?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'As a slave earnestly longs for the shade,And as a hired man eagerly
        awaits his wages,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'So am I allotted months of futility and suffering,And [long] nights
        of trouble and misery are appointed to me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "When I lie down I say,\u2018When shall I arise [and the night be
        gone]?\u2019But the night continues,And I am continually tossing until the
        dawning of day.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'My body is clothed with worms and a crust of dust;My skin is hardened
        [and broken and loathsome], and [breaks out and] runs.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "My days are swifter than a weaver\u2019s shuttle,And are spent without
        hope.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CRemember that my life is but breath [a puff of wind, a sigh];My
        eye will not see good again.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The eye of him who sees me [now] will see me no more;Your eyes will
        be upon me, but I will not be.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'As a cloud vanishes and is gone,So he who goes down to Sheol (the
        nether world, the place of the dead) does not come up.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'He will not return again to his house,Nor will his place know about
        him anymore.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CTherefore I will not restrain my mouth;I will speak in the
        anguish of my spirit,I will complain in the bitterness of my soul [O Lord].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Am I the sea, or the sea monster,That You set a guard over me?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "When I say, \u2018My bed will comfort me,My couch will ease my complaint,\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Then You frighten me with dreamsAnd terrify me through visions,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'So that I would choose suffocation,Death rather than my pain.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'I waste away and loathe my life; I will not live forever.Let me alone,
        for my days are but a breath [futile and without substance].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'What is man that You [should] magnify him [and think him important]?And
        that You are concerned about him?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And that You examine him every morningAnd try and test him every
        moment?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Will You never turn Your gaze away from me [it plagues me],Nor let
        me alone until I swallow my spittle?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'If I have sinned, what [harm] have I done to You,O Watcher of mankind?Why
        have You set me as a target for You,So that I am a burden to myself?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Why then do You not pardon my transgressionAnd take away my sin and
        guilt?For now I will lie down in the dust;And You will seek me [diligently],
        but I will not be.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Bildad Says God Rewards the Good'
      title: Bildad Says God Rewards the Good
      number: 1
      content: '  Then Bildad the Shuhite answered and said,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CHow long will you say these things?And will the words of your
        mouth be a mighty wind?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Does God pervert justice?Or does the Almighty pervert righteousness?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'If your children have sinned against Him,Then He has handed them
        over to the power of their transgression and punished them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'If you would [diligently] seek GodAnd implore the compassion and
        favor of the Almighty,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then, if you are pure and upright,Surely now He will awaken for youAnd
        restore your righteous place.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Though your beginning was insignificant,Yet your end will greatly
        increase.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CInquire, please, of past generations,And consider and apply
        yourself to the things searched out by their fathers.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'For we are only of yesterday and know nothing,Because our days on
        earth are [like] a shadow [just a breath or a vapor].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Will they (the fathers) not teach you and tell you,And utter words
        from their hearts [the deepest part of their nature]?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CCan the papyrus grow up without a marsh?Can the rushes or reed
        grass grow without water?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'While it is still green (in flower) and not cut down,Yet it withers
        before any other plant [when without water].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So are the paths of all who forget God;And the hope of the godless
        will perish,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "For his confidence is fragile and breaks,And his trust is [like]
        a spider\u2019s web.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'He trusts in his house, but it does not stand;He holds tightly to
        it, but it does not endure.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'He thrives and prospers [like a green plant] before the sun,And his
        branches spread out over his garden.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'His [godless] roots are wrapped around a pile of rocks,And he gazes
        at a house of stones.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "If he is snatched from his place [in the garden],Then his place will
        forget him, saying, \u2018I have never seen you.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Behold, this is the joy of His way;And from out of the dust others
        will spring up and grow [to take his place].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Behold, God will not reject a man of integrity,Nor will He strengthen
        or support evildoers.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'He will yet fill your mouth with laughterAnd your lips with joyful
        shouting [if you are found blameless].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Those who hate you will be clothed with shame,And the tents of the
        wicked will be no longer.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Job Says There Is No Arbitrator between God and Man'
      title: Job Says There Is No Arbitrator between God and Man
      number: 1
      content: '  Then Job answered and said,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CYes, I know it is true.But how can a mortal man be right before
        God?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'If one should want to contend or dispute with Him,He could not answer
        Him once in a thousand times.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: '  God is wise in heart and mighty in strength;Who has [ever] defied
        or challenged Him and remained unharmed?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: '  It is God who removes the mountains, and they do not know it,When
        He overturns them in His anger;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Who shakes the earth out of its place,And its pillars tremble;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Who commands the sun, and it does not shine;Who seals up the stars
        [from view];  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Who alone stretches out the heavensAnd tramples down the waves of
        the sea;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Who made [the constellations] the Bear, Orion, and the Pleiades,And
        the [vast starry] spaces of the south;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Who does great things, [beyond understanding,] unfathomable,Yes,
        marvelous and wondrous things without number.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Behold, He passes by me, and I do not see Him;He moves past me, but
        I do not perceive Him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Behold, He snatches away; who can restrain or turn Him back?Who will
        say to Him, \u2018What are You doing?\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CGod will not turn back His anger;The [proud] helpers of Rahab
        [the arrogant monster of the sea] bow under Him.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'How can I answer Him [and plead my case],Choosing my words [to reason]
        with Him?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'For though I were righteous, I could not answer.I must appeal for
        mercy to my Opponent and Judge.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'If I called and He answered me,I could not believe that He was listening
        to my voice.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'For He bruises me with a tempestAnd multiplies my wounds without
        cause.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'He will not allow me to catch my breath,But fills and saturates me
        with bitterness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'If it is a matter of strength and power, behold, He is mighty!And
        if of justice, who can summon and challenge Him?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Though I am innocent and in the right, my own mouth would pronounce
        me guilty;Though I am blameless, He would denounce me as guilty.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: '[Though] I am blameless,I do not care about myself;I despise my life.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "It is all one; therefore I say,\u2018He destroys [both] the blameless
        and the wicked.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'When [His] scourge kills suddenly,He mocks at the despair of the
        innocent.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'The earth is given into the hands of the wicked;He covers the faces
        of its judges [so that they are blind to justice].If it is not He, then who
        is it [that is responsible for all this injustice]?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CNow my days are swifter than a runner;They vanish, they see
        no good.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'They pass by like the [swift] boats made of reeds,Like an eagle that
        swoops down on its prey.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "If I say, \u2018I will forget my complaint,I will leave off my sad
        appearance, and be cheerful and brighten up,\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'I am afraid of all my pains and worries [yet to come];I know that
        You will not acquit me and leave me unpunished.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'I am accounted wicked and held guilty;Why then should I labor in
        vain [to appear innocent]?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'If I were to wash myself with snowAnd cleanse my hands with lye,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'You would still plunge me into the pit,And my own clothes would hate
        me [and refuse to cover my foul body].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'For God is not a [mere] man, as I am, that I may answer Him,That
        we may go to court and judgment together.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'There is no arbitrator between us,Who could lay his hand upon us
        both [would that there were].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Let Him take His rod away from me,And let not the dread and fear
        of Him terrify me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: '  Then I would speak [my defense] and not fear Him;But I am not like
        that in myself.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Job Despairs of God\u2019s Dealings"
      title: "Job Despairs of God\u2019s Dealings"
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CI am disgusted with my life and loathe it!I will give free
        expression to my complaint;I will speak in the bitterness of my soul.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "I will say to God, \u2018Do not condemn me [and declare me guilty]!Show
        me why You contend and argue and struggle with me.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Does it indeed seem right to You to oppress,To despise and reject
        the work of Your hands,And to look with favor on the schemes of the wicked?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Do You have eyes of flesh?Do You see as a man sees?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Are Your days as the days of a mortal,Are Your years as man\u2019s
        years,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'That You seek my guiltAnd search for my sin?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Although You know that I am not guilty or wicked,Yet there is no
        one who can rescue me from Your hand.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u2018Your hands have formed and made me altogether.Would You [turn
        around and] destroy me?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Remember now, that You have made me as clay;So will You turn me into
        dust again?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Have You not poured me out like milkAnd curdled me like cheese?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '[You have] clothed me with skin and flesh,And knit me together with
        bones and sinews.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'You have granted me life and lovingkindness;And Your providence (divine
        care, supervision) has preserved my spirit.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Yet these [present evils] You have hidden in Your heart [since my
        creation]:I know that this was within You [in Your purpose and thought].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'If I sin, then You would take note and observe me,And You would not
        acquit me of my guilt.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'If I am wicked, woe to me [for judgment comes]!And if I am righteous,
        I dare not lift up my head.For I am sated and filled with disgrace and the
        sight of my misery.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Should I lift my head up, You would hunt me like a lion;And again
        You would show Your marvelous power against me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'You renew Your witnesses against meAnd increase Your indignation
        and anger toward me;Hardship after hardship is with me [attacking me time
        after time].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u2018Why then did You bring me out of the womb?Would that I had
        perished and no eye had seen me!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "I should have been as though I had not existed;[I should have been]
        carried from the womb to the grave.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Would He not let my few days alone,Withdraw from me that I may have
        a little cheer  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Before I go\u2014and I shall not return\u2014To the land of darkness
        and the deep shadow [of death],  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "The [sunless] land of utter gloom as darkness itself,[The land] of
        the shadow of death, without order,And [where] it shines as [thick] darkness.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Zophar Rebukes Job'
      title: Zophar Rebukes Job
      number: 1
      content: '  Then Zophar the Naamathite answered and said,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CShall a multitude of words not be answered?And should a talkative
        man [making such a long-winded defense] be acquitted?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Should your boasts and babble silence men?And shall you scoff and
        no one put you to shame?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "For you have said, \u2018My teaching (doctrine) [that God knowingly
        afflicts the righteous] is pure,And I am innocent in your eyes.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'But oh, that God would speak,And open His lips [to speak] against
        you,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And [that He would] show you the secrets of wisdom!For sound wisdom
        has two sides.Know therefore that God forgets a part of your wickedness and
        guilt.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CCan you discover the depths of God?Can you [by searching] discover
        the limits of the Almighty [ascend to His heights, extend to His widths,
        and comprehend His infinite perfection]?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: '  His wisdom is as high as the heights of heaven. What can you do?It
        is deeper than Sheol (the nether world, the place of the dead). What can
        you know?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'It is longer in measure [and scope] than the earth,And broader than
        the sea.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'If God passes by or arrests,Or calls an assembly [of judgment], who
        can restrain Him?[If He is against a man, who can call Him to account for
        it?]  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'For He recognizes and knows false and worthless men,And He sees wickedness,
        will He not consider it?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'But a hollow (empty-headed) man will become intelligent and wise[Only]
        when the colt of a wild donkey is born as a man.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CIf you direct your heart [on the right path]And stretch out
        your hands to Him,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'If sin is in your hand, put it far away [from you],And do not let
        wrongdoing dwell in your tents;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Then, indeed, you could lift up your face [to Him] without moral
        defect,And you would be firmly established and secure and not fear.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'For you would forget your trouble;You would remember it as waters
        that have passed by.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And your life would be brighter than the noonday;Darkness [then]
        would be like the morning.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Then you would trust [with confidence], because there is hope;You
        would look around you and rest securely.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'You would lie down with no one to frighten you,And many would entreat
        and seek your favor.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "But the eyes of the wicked will fail,And they will not escape [the
        justice of God];And their hope is to breathe their last [and die].\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Job Chides His Accusers'
      title: Job Chides His Accusers
      number: 1
      content: '  Then Job responded,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CNo doubt you are the [only wise] people [in the world],And
        wisdom will die with you!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "But I have intelligence and understanding as well as you;I am not
        inferior to you.Who does not know such things as these [of God\u2019s wisdom
        and might]?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "I am a joke to my friends;I, one whom God answered when he called
        upon Him\u2014A just and blameless man is a joke [and laughed to scorn].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'He who is at ease has contempt for misfortune,  But misfortune is
        ready [and anxiously waiting] for those whose feet slip.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'The tents of the destroyers prosper;And those who provoke God are
        [apparently] secure,Whom God brings into their power.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CNow ask the animals, and let them teach you [that God does
        not deal with His creatures according to their character];And ask the birds
        of the air, and let them tell you;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Or speak to the earth [with its many forms of life], and it will
        teach you;And let the fish of the sea declare [this truth] to you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Who among all these does not recognize [in all these things that
        good and evil are randomly scattered throughout nature and human life]That
        the hand of the Lord has done this,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'In whose hand is the life of every living thing,And the breath of
        all mankind?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Does the ear not put words to the test,Just as the palate tastes
        its food [distinguishing between the desirable and the undesirable]?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: Job Speaks of the Power of God'
      title: Job Speaks of the Power of God
      number: 12
      content: 'With the aged [you say] is wisdom,And with  long life is understanding.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CBut [only] with Him are [perfect] wisdom and might;He [alone]
        has [true] counsel and understanding.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Behold, He tears down, and it cannot be rebuilt;He imprisons a man,
        and there can be no release.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Behold, He restrains the waters, and they dry up;Again, He sends
        the waters out, and they overwhelm and devastate the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'With Him are might and sound wisdom,The misled and the misleader
        are His [and in His power].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'He makes [great and scheming] counselors walk barefootAnd makes fools
        of judges.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'He loosens the bond of kingsAnd binds their loins with a loincloth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'He makes priests walk barefoot,And He overturns men firmly seated
        and secure.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'He deprives the trusted ones of speechAnd takes away the discernment
        and discretion of the aged.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'He pours contempt on princes and noblesAnd loosens the belt of the
        strong [disabling them].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'He uncovers mysteries [that are difficult to grasp and understand]
        out of the darknessAnd brings black gloom and the shadow of death into light.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'He makes nations great, and He destroys them;He enlarges nations,
        and leads them away [captive].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'He removes intelligence and understanding from the leaders of the
        people of the earthAnd makes them wander and move blindly in a pathless waste.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "They grope in darkness without light,And He makes them stagger like
        a drunken man.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Job Says His Friends\u2019 Proverbs Are Ashes"
      title: "Job Says His Friends\u2019 Proverbs Are Ashes"
      number: 1
      content: "  [Job continued:] \u201CBehold, my eye has seen all this,My ear
        has heard and understood it.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'What you know I also know;I am not inferior to you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CBut I wish to speak to the Almighty,And I desire to argue with
        God.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'But you smear me with lies [you defame my character most untruthfully];You
        are all worthless physicians and have no remedy to offer.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Oh, that you would be completely silent,And that silence would be
        your wisdom!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Please hear my argumentAnd listen to the pleadings of my lips.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Will you speak what is unjust for God,And speak what is deceitful
        for Him?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Will you show partiality for Him [and be unjust to me so that you
        may gain favor with Him]?Will you contend and plead for God?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Will it be well for you when He investigates you [and your tactics
        against me]?Or will you deceive Him as one deceives a man?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'He will surely reprimand youIf you secretly show partiality.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Will not His majesty terrify you,And will not the dread of Him fall
        upon you?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: Job Is Sure He Will Be Vindicated'
      title: Job Is Sure He Will Be Vindicated
      number: 12
      content: 'Your memorable sayings are [worthless, merely] proverbs of ashes;Your
        defenses are defenses of [crumbling] clay.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CBe silent before me so that I may speak;And let happen to me
        what may.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Why should I take my flesh in my teethAnd put my life in my hands
        [incurring the wrath of God]?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Even though He kills me;I will hope in Him.Nevertheless, I will argue
        my ways to His face.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'This also will be my salvation,For a godless man may not come before
        Him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Listen diligently to my speech,And let my declaration fill your ears.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Behold now, I have prepared my case;I know that I will be vindicated.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Who will argue and contend with me?For then I would be silent and
        die.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201COnly [O Lord,] do not do two things to me,And then I will not
        hide myself from Your face:  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Withdraw Your hand from me and remove this bodily suffering,And let
        not the dread of You terrify me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Then [Lord,] call, and I will answer;Or let me speak, and then reply
        to me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'How many are my iniquities and sins [that so much sorrow should come
        to me]?Make me recognize and understand my transgression and my sin.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Why do You hide Your face [as if offended]And consider me Your enemy?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Will You cause a windblown leaf to tremble?Will You pursue the chaff
        of the dry stubble?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'For You write bitter things against me [in Your indictment]And make
        me inherit and suffer for the iniquities of my youth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'You also put my feet in the stocks [as punishment]And [critically]
        observe all my paths;You set a circle and limit around the soles of my feet
        [which I must not overstep],  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: While I waste away like a rotten thing,Like a garment that is moth-eaten.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Job Speaks of the Finality of Death'
      title: Job Speaks of the Finality of Death
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CMan, who is born of a woman,Is short-lived and full of turmoil.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Like a flower he comes forth and withers;He also flees like a shadow
        and does not remain.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'You also open Your eyes upon himAnd bring him into judgment with
        Yourself.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Who can make a clean thing out of the unclean?No one!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Since his days are determined,The number of his months is with You
        [in Your control],And You have made his limits so he cannot pass [his allotted
        time].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '[O God] turn your gaze from him so that he may rest,Until he fulfills
        his day [on earth] like a hired man.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CFor there is hope for a tree,If it is cut down, that it will
        sprout again,And that the shoots of it will not cease nor fail, [but there
        is no such hope for man].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Though its roots grow old in the earthAnd its stump dies in the dry
        soil,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Yet at the scent of water [the stump of the tree] will flourishAnd
        bring forth sprigs and shoots like a seedling.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'But [the brave, strong] man must die and lie face down;Man breathes
        his last, and where is he?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'As water evaporates from the sea,And a river drains and dries up,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'So man lies down and does not rise [again].Until the heavens are
        no longer,  The dead will not awake nor be raised from their sleep.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201COh, that You would hide me in Sheol (the nether world, the
        place of the dead),That You would conceal me until Your wrath is past,That
        You would set a definite time and then remember me [and in Your lovingkindness
        imprint me on your heart]!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'If a man dies, will he live again?I will wait all the days of my
        struggleUntil my change and release will come.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: '[Then] You will call, and I will answer You;You will long for [me]
        the work of Your hands.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'But now You number [each of] my steps;You do not observe nor take
        note of my sin.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'My transgression is sealed up in a bag,And You cover my wickedness
        [from Your view].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CBut as a mountain, if it falls, crumbles into nothing,And as
        the rock is moved from its place,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Water wears away the stones,Its floods and torrents wash away the
        soil of the earth,So You [O Lord] destroy the hope of man.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'You prevail forever against him and overpower him, and he passes
        on;You change his appearance and send him away [from the presence of the
        living].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'His sons achieve honor, and he does not know it;They become insignificant,
        and he is not aware of it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "But his body [lamenting its decay] grieves in pain over it,And his
        soul mourns over [the loss of] himself.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Eliphaz Says Job Presumes Much'
      title: Eliphaz Says Job Presumes Much
      number: 1
      content: '  Then Eliphaz the Temanite answered [Job] and said,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CShould a wise man [such as you] utter such windy and vain knowledge
        [as we have just heard]And fill himself with the east wind [of withering,
        parching, and violent accusations]?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Should he rebuke and argue with useless talk?Or with words in which
        there is no benefit?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Indeed, you are doing away with fear,And you are diminishing meditation
        before God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'For your guilt teaches your mouth,And you choose [to speak] the language
        of the crafty and cunning.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Your own mouth condemns you, and not I;Yes, your own lips testify
        against you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CWere you the first man to be born [the original wise man],Or
        were you created before the hills?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Do you hear the secret counsel of God,And do you limit [the possession
        of] wisdom to yourself?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'What do you know that we do not know?  What do you understand that
        is not equally clear to us?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Among us are both the gray-haired and the aged,Older than your father.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Are the consolations of God [as we have interpreted them to you]
        too trivial for you,[Or] were we too gentle toward you [in our first speech]
        to be effective?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Why does your heart carry you away [allowing you to be controlled
        by emotion]?And why do your eyes flash [in anger or contempt],  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'That you should turn your spirit against GodAnd let such words [as
        you have spoken] go out of your mouth?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'What is man, that he should be pure and clean,Or he who is born of
        a woman, that he should be righteous and just?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Behold, God puts no trust in His holy ones (angels);Indeed, the heavens
        are not pure in His sight\u2014  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: What Eliphaz Has Seen of Life'
      title: What Eliphaz Has Seen of Life
      number: 16
      content: 'How much less [pure and clean is] the one who is repulsive and corrupt,Man,
        who drinks unrighteousness and injustice like water!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CI will tell you, listen to me;And what I have seen I will also
        declare;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'What wise men have [freely] told,And have not hidden [anything passed
        on to them] from their fathers,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'To whom alone the land was given,And no stranger passed among them
        [corrupting the truth].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'The wicked man writhes with pain all his days,And numbered are the
        years stored up for him, the ruthless one.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'A [dreadful] sound of terrors is in his ears;While at peace and in
        a time of prosperity the destroyer comes upon him [the tent of the robber
        is not at peace].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "He does not believe that he will return out of the darkness [for
        fear of being murdered],And he is destined for the sword [of God\u2019s vengeance].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "He wanders about for food, saying, \u2018Where is it?\u2019He knows
        that the day of darkness and destruction is already at hand.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Distress and anxiety terrify him,They overpower him like a king ready
        for battle.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Because he has stretched out his hand against GodAnd behaves arrogantly
        against the Almighty,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Running and charging headlong against HimWith his ornamented and
        massive shield;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'For he has covered his face with his fat,Adding layers of fat to
        his thighs [giving himself up to pleasures],  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And he has lived in desolate [God-forsaken] cities,In houses which
        no one should inhabit,Which were destined to become heaps [of ruins];  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'He will not become rich, nor will his wealth endure;And his grain
        will not bend to the earth nor his possessions be extended on the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "He will not escape from darkness [fleeing disaster];The flame [of
        God\u2019s wrath] will wither his branch,And by the blast of His mouth he
        will go away.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Let him not trust in vanity (emptiness, futility) and be led astray;For
        emptiness will be his reward [for such living].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'It will be fulfilled while he still lives,And his branch will not
        be green [but shall wither away].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'He will fail to bring his grapes to maturity [leaving them to wither
        unnourished] on the vine,And will cast off blossoms [and fail to bring forth
        fruit] like the olive tree.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'For the company of the godless is barren,And fire consumes the tents
        of bribery (wrong and injustice).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "They conceive mischief and bring forth wickedness,And their inmost
        soul prepares deceit and fraud.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Job Says Friends Are Sorry Comforters'
      title: Job Says Friends Are Sorry Comforters
      number: 1
      content: '  Then Job answered and said,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CI have heard many such things;Wearisome and miserable comforters
        are you all.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Is there no end to [your futile] words of wind?Or what plagues you
        [so much] that you [so boldly] answer [me like this]?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'I also could speak like you,If you were in my place;I could compose
        and join words together against youAnd shake my head at you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: Job Says God Shattered Him'
      title: Job Says God Shattered Him
      number: 5
      content: '[But instead] I could strengthen and encourage you with [the words
        of] my mouth,And the consolation and solace of my lips would soothe your
        suffering and lessen your anguish.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CIf I speak [to you miserable comforters], my pain is not relieved;And
        if I refrain [from speaking], what [pain or anguish] leaves me?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'But now God has exhausted me.You [O Lord] have destroyed all my family
        and my household.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'You have taken a firm hold on me and have shriveled me up,It has
        become a witness [against me];And my leanness [and infirmity] rises up [as
        evidence] against me,It testifies to my face [about my guilt].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'His wrath has torn me and hunted me down,He has gnashed at me with
        his teeth;My adversary sharpens His gaze and glares [with piercing eyes]
        at me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'They have gaped at me with their mouths,With contempt they have struck
        me on the cheek;They massed themselves together [and conspired] against me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'God hands me over to criminalsAnd tosses me [headlong] into the hands
        of the wicked.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'I was [living] at ease, but He crushed me and broke me apart,And
        He has seized me by the neck and has shaken me to pieces;He has also set
        me up as His target.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'His arrows surround me.He pierces my kidneys (vital organs) without
        mercy;He pours out my gall on the ground.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'He attacks me, making wound after wound;He runs at me like a warrior.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'I have sewed sackcloth over my skin [as a sign of mourning]And have
        defiled my horn (symbol of strength) in the dust.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'My face is red and swollen with weeping,And on my eyelids is the
        shadow of death [my eyes are dimmed],  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Although there is no violence or wrongdoing in my hands,And my prayer
        is pure.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CO earth, do not cover my blood,And let there be no [resting]
        place for my cry [where it will cease being heard].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Even now, behold, my Witness is in heaven,And my Advocate [who vouches
        and testifies for me] is on high.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'My friends are scoffers [who ridicule];My eye pours out tears to
        God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Oh, that a man would mediate and plead with God [for me]Just as a
        man [mediates and pleads] with his neighbor and friend.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: For when a few years are past,I shall go the way of no return.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Job Says He Has Become a Byword'
      title: Job Says He Has Become a Byword
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CMy spirit is broken, my days are extinguished,The grave is
        ready for me.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Surely there are mockers and mockery with me,And my eye gazes on
        their obstinacy and provocation.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CGive me a pledge (guarantee, promise) with Yourself [acknowledge
        my innocence before my death];Who is there that will be my guarantor and
        give security for me?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'But You [Lord] have closed their hearts to understanding,Therefore
        You will not exalt them [by giving a verdict against me].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'He who denounces and informs against his friends for a share of the
        spoil,The eyes of his children will also languish and fail.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CBut He has made me a byword and mockery among the people,And
        I have become one in whose face people spit.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "My eye has grown dim (unexpressive) because of grief,And all my [body\u2019s]
        members are [wasted away] like a shadow.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The upright will be [astonished and] appalled at this,And the innocent
        will stir himself up against the godless and polluted.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Nevertheless the righteous will hold to his ways,And he who has clean
        hands will grow stronger and stronger.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'But as for all of you, come back again,Even though I do not find
        a wise man among you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'My days are past, my purposes and plans are frustrated and torn apart;The
        wishes of my heart [are broken].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "These [thoughts try to] make the night into the day;\u2018The light
        is near,\u2019 they say in the presence of darkness [but they pervert the
        truth].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'But if I look to Sheol (the nether world, the place of the dead)
        as my home,If I make my bed in the darkness,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "If I call out to the pit (grave), \u2018You are my father\u2019;And
        to the worm [that feeds on decay], \u2018You are my mother and my sister
        [because I will soon be closest to you],\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Where now is my hope?And who regards or considers or is even concerned
        about my hope?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Will my hope go down with me to Sheol (the nether world, the place
        of the dead)?Shall we go down together in the dust?\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Bildad Speaks of the Wicked'
      title: Bildad Speaks of the Wicked
      number: 1
      content: '  Then Bildad the Shuhite answered and said,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CHow long will you hunt for words and continue these speeches?Do
        some clear thinking and show understanding and then we can talk.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Why are we regarded as beasts,As if [we are] stupid (senseless) in
        your eyes?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'You who tear yourself apart in anger,Is the earth to be abandoned
        for your sake,Or the rock to be moved out of its place?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CIndeed, the light of the wicked will be put out,And the flame
        of his fire will not shine.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'The light will be dark in his tent,And his lamp beside him will be
        put out.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The vigorous stride will be shortened,And his own counsel and the
        scheme [in which he trusted] will bring his downfall.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'For the wicked is thrown into a net by his own feet (wickedness),And
        he steps on the webbing [of the lattice-covered pit].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'A snare catches him by the heel,And a trap snaps shut on him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'A noose is hidden for him on the ground,And a trap for him on the
        path.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Terrors frighten him on every sideAnd chase at his heels.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The strength [of the wicked] is famished and weakened,And disaster
        is ready at his side [if he stops].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'His skin is devoured by disease;The firstborn of death [the worst
        of diseases] consumes his limbs.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'He is torn from his tent which he trusted [for safety],And he is
        marched and brought to the king of terrors (death).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Nothing of his dwells in his tent;Brimstone (burning sulfur) is scattered
        over his dwelling [to purify it].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'The roots [of the wicked] are dried up below,And above, his branch
        is cut off and withers.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Memory of him perishes from the earth,And he has no name on the street.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'He is driven and propelled from light into darkness,And chased from
        the inhabited world.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'He has no offspring or prosperity among his people,Nor any survivor
        where he sojourned.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Those in the west are astonished and appalled at his fate,And those
        in the east are seized with horror.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Surely such are the dwellings of the wicked and the ungodly,And such
        is the place of him who does not know or recognize or honor God.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Job Feels Insulted'
      title: Job Feels Insulted
      number: 1
      content: '  Then Job answered and said,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CHow long will you torment and exasperate meAnd crush me with
        words?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'These ten times you have insulted me;You are not ashamed to wrong
        me [and harden your hearts against me].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And if it were true that I have erred,My error would remain with
        me [and I would be conscious of it].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'If indeed you [braggarts] vaunt and magnify yourselves over meAnd
        prove my disgrace (humiliation) to me,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: Everything Is Against Him'
      title: Everything Is Against Him
      number: 6
      content: 'Know then that God has wronged me and overthrown meAnd has closed
        His net around me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CBehold, I cry out, \u2018Violence!\u2019 but I am not heard;I
        shout for help, but there is no justice.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'He has walled up my way so that I cannot pass,And He has set darkness
        upon my paths.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'He has stripped me of my honorAnd removed the crown from my head.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'He breaks me down on every side, and I am gone;He has uprooted my
        hope like a tree.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'He has also kindled His wrath [like a fire] against meAnd He considers
        and counts me as one of His adversaries.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'His troops come togetherAnd build up their way and siege works against
        meAnd camp around my tent.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CHe has put my brothers far from me,And my acquaintances are
        completely estranged from me.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'My relatives have failed [me],And my intimate friends have forgotten
        me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Those who live [temporarily] in my house and my maids consider me
        a stranger;I am a foreigner in their sight.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'I call to my servant, but he does not answer;I have to implore him
        with words.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'My breath is repulsive to my wife,And I am loathsome to my own brothers.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Even young children despise me;When I get up, they speak against
        me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'All the men of my council hate me;Those I love have turned against
        me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'My bone clings to my skin and to my flesh,And I have escaped [death]
        by the skin of my teeth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Have pity on me! Have pity on me, O you my friends,For the hand of
        God has touched me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: "22: Job Says, \u201CMy Redeemer Lives\u201D"
      title: "Job Says, \u201CMy Redeemer Lives\u201D"
      number: 22
      content: 'Why do you persecute me as God does?Why are you not satisfied with
        my flesh (anguish)?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "\u201COh, that the words I now speak were written!Oh, that they were
        recorded in a scroll!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'That with an iron stylus and [molten] leadThey were engraved in the
        rock forever!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'For I know that my Redeemer and Vindicator lives,And at the last
        He will take His stand upon the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Even after my [mortal] skin is destroyed [by death],Yet from my [immortal]
        flesh I will see God,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Whom I, even I, will see for myself,And my eyes will see Him and
        not another!My heart faints within me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "If you say, \u2018How shall we [continue to] persecute him?\u2019And
        \u2018What pretext for a case against him can we find [since we claim the
        root of these afflictions is found in him]?\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "  Then beware and be afraid of the sword [of divine vengeance] for
        yourselves,For wrathful are the punishments of that sword,So that you may
        know there is judgment.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Zophar Says, \u201CThe Triumph of the Wicked Is Short\u201D"
      title: "Zophar Says, \u201CThe Triumph of the Wicked Is Short\u201D"
      number: 1
      content: '  Then Zophar the Naamathite answered and said,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CTherefore my disquieting thoughts make me answer,Because of
        the uneasiness that is within me.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'I have heard the reproof which insults me,But the spirit of my understanding
        makes me answer.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Do you not know this from the old days,Since the time that man was
        placed on the earth,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'That the triumphing of the wicked is short,And the joy of the godless
        is only for a moment?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Though his pride reaches the heavensAnd his head touches the clouds,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "  Yet he perishes forever like his own refuse;Those who have seen
        him will say, \u2018Where is he?\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'He flies away like a dream and cannot be found;Yes, he is chased
        away like a vision of the night.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The eye which saw him sees him no longer,Neither does his [accustomed]
        place behold him any longer.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'His sons favor the poor [and pay his obligations],And his hands give
        back his [ill-gotten] wealth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'His bones are full of youthful strengthBut it lies down with him
        in the dust.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CThough evil and wickedness are sweet in his mouthAnd he hides
        it under his tongue,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Though he desires it and will not let it goBut holds it in his mouth,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: '  Yet his food turns [to poison] in his stomach;It is the venom of
        vipers within him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'He swallows [his ill-gotten] riches,But will vomit them up;God will
        drive them out of his belly.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "He sucks the poison of vipers [which ill-gotten wealth contains];The
        viper\u2019s tongue slays him.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'He does not look at the rivers,The flowing streams of honey and butter
        [to enjoy his wealth].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'He gives back what he has labored for and attainedAnd cannot swallow
        it [down to enjoy it];As to the riches of his labor,He cannot even enjoy
        them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'For he has oppressed and neglected the poor;He has violently taken
        away houses which he did not build.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CBecause he knew no quietness or calm within him [because of
        his greed],He does not retain anything he desires.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'There is nothing left of what he devoured;Therefore his prosperity
        does not endure.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'In the fullness of his excess (great abundance) he will be in trouble;The
        hand of everyone who suffers will come against him [he is miserable on every
        side].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'When he fills his belly,  God will send His fierce anger on himAnd
        will rain it upon him while he is eating.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'He may flee from the iron weapon,  But the bow of bronze will pierce
        him through.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: '  The arrow is drawn forth and it comes out of his back [after passing
        through his body];Yes, the glittering point comes out of his gall.Terrors
        march in upon him;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Complete darkness (misfortune) is held in reserve for his treasures.An
        unfanned fire will devour him;It will consume the survivor in his tent.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'The heavens will reveal his wickedness and guilt,And the earth will
        rise up against him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "The produce and increase of his house will depart [with the victors]; 
        His possessions will be dragged away in the day of God\u2019s wrath.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "This is the wicked man\u2019s portion from God,And the heritage decreed
        and appointed to him by God.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Job\u2019s Dialogue Regarding the Wicked"
      title: "Job\u2019s Dialogue Regarding the Wicked"
      number: 1
      content: '  Then Job answered and said,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CListen carefully to my speech,And let this be the consolation.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Bear with me, and I also will speak;And after I have spoken, you
        may [continue to] mock [me].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'As for me, is my complaint to man or about him?And why should I not
        be impatient and my spirit troubled?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Look at me and be astonished and appalled;And put your hand over
        your mouth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Even when I remember, I am troubled and afraid;Horror and trembling
        take hold of my flesh.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Why do the wicked still live,Become old, and become mighty in power?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Their children and descendants are established with them in their
        sight,And their offspring before their eyes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Their houses are safe from fear;And the rod of God is not on them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'His bull breeds and does not fail;His cow calves and does not miscarry.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'They send forth their little ones like a flock,And their children
        skip about.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'They lift up their voices and sing to the tambourine and the lyreAnd
        rejoice to the sound of the flute.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'They fully enjoy their days in prosperity,And so go down to Sheol
        (the nether world, the place of the dead) in a [peaceful] moment.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Yet they say to God, \u2018Depart from us,For we do not desire the
        knowledge of Your ways.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Who [and what] is the Almighty, that we should serve Him?And what
        would we gain if we plead with Him?\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "  But notice, the prosperity of the wicked is not in their hand (in
        their power);The counsel of the wicked [and the mystery of God\u2019s dealings
        with the ungodly] is far from my comprehension.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CHow often [then] is it that the lamp of the wicked is put out,And
        that their disaster falls on them?Does God distribute pain and destruction
        and sorrow [to them] in His anger?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Are they like straw before the wind,And like chaff that the storm
        steals and carries away?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "  You say, \u2018God stores away [the punishment of] man\u2019s wickedness
        for his children.\u2019Let God repay him so that he may know and experience
        it.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Let his own eyes see his destruction,And let him drink of the wrath
        of the Almighty.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'For what pleasure does he have in his house and family after he is
        dead,When the number of his months [of life] is cut off?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Can anyone teach God knowledge,Seeing that He judges those on high?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'One dies in his full strength,Being wholly at ease and quiet and
        satisfied;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'His pails are full of milk [his sides are filled out with fat],And
        the marrow of his bones is moist,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Whereas another dies with a bitter soul,Never even tasting pleasure
        or good fortune.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Together they lie down in the dust,And the worms cover them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "\u201CBehold, I know your thoughts,And the plots by which you would
        wrong me.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "For you say, \u2018Where is the house of the noble man?And where
        is the tent, the dwelling place of the wicked?\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Have you not asked those who travel this way,And do you not recognize
        their witness?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "That evil men are [now] reserved for the day of disaster and destruction,They
        will be led away on the day of [God\u2019s] wrath?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: '  But who will confront him with his actions and rebuke him face
        to face,And who will repay him for what he has done?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'When he is carried to his grave,  A guard will keep watch over his
        tomb.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'The [dirt] clods of the valley are sweet to him [and gently cover
        him],Moreover, all men will follow after him [to a grave],While countless
        ones go before him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "How then can you vainly comfort me with empty words,Since your answers
        remain untrue?\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Eliphaz Accuses and Exhorts Job'
      title: Eliphaz Accuses and Exhorts Job
      number: 1
      content: '  Then Eliphaz the Temanite answered and said,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CCan a vigorous man be of use to God,Or a wise man be useful
        to himself?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Is it any pleasure or joy to the Almighty that you are righteous?Or
        is it of benefit to Him that you make your ways perfect?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Is it because of your fear of Him that He corrects you,That He enters
        into judgment against you?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Is not your wickedness great,And your sins without end?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'For you have taken pledges of your brothers without cause,And stripped
        men naked.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'You have not given water to the weary to drink,And you have withheld
        bread from the hungry.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'But the land is possessed by the man with power,And the favored and
        honorable man dwells in it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'You have sent widows away empty-handed,And the arms (strength) of
        the fatherless have been broken.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Therefore snares surround you,And sudden dread terrifies and overwhelms
        you;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Or darkness, so that you cannot see,And a flood of water covers you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CIs not God in the height of heaven?And behold the distant stars,
        how high they are!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "You say, \u2018What does God know [about me]?Can He judge through
        the thick darkness?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Thick clouds are a hiding place for Him, so that He cannot see,And
        He walks on the vault (circle) of the heavens.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Will you keep to the ancient pathThat wicked men walked [in the time
        of Noah],  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Men who were snatched away before their time,Whose foundations were
        poured out like a river?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "They said to God, \u2018Depart from us!What can the Almighty do for
        us or to us?\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Yet He filled their houses with good things;But the counsel of the
        wicked and ungodly is far from me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'The righteous see it and are glad;And the innocent mock and laugh
        at them, saying,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u2018Surely our adversaries are cut off and destroyed,And fire has
        consumed their abundance.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CNow yield and submit yourself to Him [agree with God and be
        conformed to His will] and be at peace;In this way [you will prosper and
        great] good will come to you.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Please receive the law and instruction from His mouthAnd establish
        His words in your heart and keep them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'If you return to the Almighty [and submit and humble yourself before
        Him], you will be built up [and restored];  If you remove unrighteousness
        far from your tents,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And place your gold in the dust,And the gold of Ophir among the stones
        of the brooks [considering it of little value],  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And make the Almighty your goldAnd your precious silver,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Then you will have delight in the Almighty,And you will lift up your
        face to God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'You will pray to Him, and He will hear you,And you will pay your
        vows.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "You will also decide and decree a thing, and it will be established
        for you;And the light [of God\u2019s favor] will shine upon your ways.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'When you are cast down and humbled, you will speak with confidence,And
        the humble person He will lift up and save.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "He will even rescue the one [for whom you intercede] who is not innocent;And
        he will be rescued through the cleanness of your hands.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Job Says He Longs for God'
      title: Job Says He Longs for God
      number: 1
      content: '  Then Job answered and said,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CEven today my complaint is contentious;His hand is heavy despite
        my groaning.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Oh, that I knew where I might find Him,That I might [even] come to
        His seat!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'I would present my cause before HimAnd fill my mouth with arguments.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'I would learn the words which He would answer,And understand what
        He would say to me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Would He contend against me with His great power?No, surely He would
        give attention to me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'There the righteous and upright could reason with Him;So I would
        be acquitted forever by my Judge.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CBehold, I go forward (to the east), but He is not there;I go
        backward (to the west), but I cannot perceive Him;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'To the left (north) He turns, but I cannot behold Him;He turns to
        the right hand (south), but I cannot see Him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'But He knows the way that I take [and He pays attention to it]. 
        When He has tried me, I will come forth as [refined] gold [pure and luminous].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'My feet have carefully followed His steps;I have kept His ways and
        not turned aside.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'I have not departed from the commandment of His lips;I have kept
        the words of His mouth more than my necessary food.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'But He is unique and unchangeable, and who can turn Him?And what
        His soul desires, that He does.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'For He performs what is planned (appointed) for me,And He is mindful
        of many such things.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Therefore I would be terrified at His presence;  When I consider
        [all of this], I tremble in dread of Him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'For God has made my heart faint,And the Almighty has terrified me,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: But I am not silenced by the darkness [of these woes that fell on
        me],Nor by the thick darkness which covers my face.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Job Says God Seems to Ignore Wrongs'
      title: Job Says God Seems to Ignore Wrongs
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CWhy does the Almighty not set seasons for judgment?Why do
        those who know Him not see His days [for punishment of the wicked]?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Some remove the landmarks;They [violently] seize and pasture flocks
        [appropriating land and flocks openly].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "They drive away the donkeys of the orphans;They take the widow\u2019s
        ox for a pledge.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'They crowd the needy off the road;The poor of the land all hide themselves.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Behold, as wild donkeys in the desert,The poor go to their work,
        diligently seeking food;As bread for their children in the desert.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'They harvest their fodder in a field [that is not their own],And
        glean the vineyard of the wicked.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'They spend the night naked, without clothing,And have no covering
        against the cold.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'They are wet from the rain of the mountainsAnd cling to the rock
        for lack of shelter.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Others snatch the fatherless [infants] from the breast [to sell or
        make them slaves],And against the poor they take a pledge [of clothing].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'They cause the poor to go about naked without clothing,And they take
        away the sheaves [of grain] from the hungry.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Within the walls [of the wicked] the poor make [olive] oil;They tread
        [the grapes in] the wine presses, but thirst.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'From the [populous and crowded] city men groan,And the souls of the
        wounded cry out for help;Yet God [seemingly] does not pay attention to the
        wrong [done to them].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201COthers have been with those who rebel against the light;They
        do not want to know its waysNor stay in its paths.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'The murderer rises at dawn;He kills the poor and the needy,And at
        night he becomes a thief.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "The eye of the adulterer waits for the twilight,Saying, \u2018No
        eye will see me,\u2019And he covers his face.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'In the dark they dig into [the penetrable walls of] houses;They shut
        themselves up by day;They do not know the light [of day].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'For the morning is the same to him as the thick darkness [of midnight];For
        he is familiar with the terrors of thick darkness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CThey are insignificant on the surface of the water;Their portion
        is cursed on the earth;They do not turn toward the vineyards.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Drought and heat consume the snow waters;  So does Sheol (the nether
        world, the place of the dead) [consume] those who have sinned.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'A mother will forget him;The worm feeds on him until he is no longer
        remembered.And wickedness will be broken like a tree [which cannot be restored].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'He preys on the barren (childless) womanAnd does no good for the
        widow.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Yet God draws away the mighty by His power;He rises, but no one has
        assurance of life.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'God gives them security, and they are supported;And His eyes are
        on their ways.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'They are exalted for a little while, and then they are gone;Moreover,
        they are brought low and like everything [they are] gathered up and taken
        out of the way;Even like the heads of grain they are cut off.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "And if this is not so, who can prove me a liarAnd make my speech
        worthless?\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Bildad Says Man Is Inferior'
      title: Bildad Says Man Is Inferior
      number: 1
      content: '  Then Bildad the Shuhite answered and said,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CDominion and awe belong to God;He establishes peace and order
        in His high places.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Is there any number to His [vast celestial] armies?And upon whom
        does His light not rise?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'How then can man be justified and righteous with God?Or how can he
        who is born of a woman be pure and clean?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Behold, even the moon has no brightness [compared to God\u2019s majesty
        and glory]And the stars are not pure in His sight,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "How much less man, that maggot,And the son of man, that worm!\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Job Rebukes Bildad'
      title: Job Rebukes Bildad
      number: 1
      content: '  But Job answered and said,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CWhat a help you are to the weak (powerless)!How you have saved
        the arm that is without strength!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'How you have counseled the one who has no wisdom!And how abundantly
        you have provided sound wisdom and helpful insight!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: The Greatness of God'
      title: The Greatness of God
      number: 4
      content: 'To whom have you uttered [these] words?And whose spirit [inspired
        what] came forth from you?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CThe spirits of the dead trembleUnderneath the waters and their
        inhabitants.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Sheol (the nether world, the place of the dead) is naked before God,And
        Abaddon (the place of destruction) has no covering [from His eyes].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: '  It is He who spreads out the north over emptinessAnd hangs the
        earth on nothing.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'He wraps the waters in His clouds [which otherwise would spill on
        earth all at once],And the cloud does not burst under them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'He covers the face of the full moonAnd spreads His cloud over it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'He has inscribed a circular limit (the horizon) on the face of the
        watersAt the boundary between light and darkness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'The pillars of the heavens trembleAnd are terrified at His rebuke.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'He stirred up the sea by His power,And by His understanding He smashed
        [proud] Rahab.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'By His breath the heavens are cleared;His hand has pierced the [swiftly]
        fleeing serpent.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Yet these are just the fringes of His ways [mere samples of His power],The
        faintest whisper of His voice!Who can contemplate the thunder of His [full]
        mighty power?\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Job Affirms His Righteousness'
      title: Job Affirms His Righteousness
      number: 1
      content: '  Job continued his discourse and said,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CAs God lives, who has taken away my right and denied me justice,And
        the Almighty, who has caused bitterness and grief for my soul,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'As long as my life is within me,And the breath of God is [still]
        in my nostrils,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'My lips will not speak unjustly,Nor will my tongue utter deceit.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Far be it from me that I should admit you are right [in your accusations
        against me];Until I die, I will not remove my integrity from me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: The State of the Godless'
      title: The State of the Godless
      number: 6
      content: 'I hold fast my uprightness and my right standing with God and I will
        not let them go;My heart does not reproach me for any of my days.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CMay my enemy be as the wicked,And he who rises up against me
        be as the unrighteous (unjust).  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'For what is the hope of the godless, even though he has gained [in
        this world],When God takes his life?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Will God hear his cryWhen trouble and distress come upon him?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Will he take delight in the Almighty?Will he call on God at all times?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "I will teach you regarding the hand (power) of God;I will not conceal
        what is with the Almighty [God\u2019s actual treatment of the wicked].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Behold, all of you have seen it;Why then do you act vainly and foolishly
        [cherishing worthless concepts]?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CThis [which I am about to explain] is the portion of a wicked
        man from God,And the inheritance which tyrants and oppressors receive from
        the Almighty:  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Though his children are many, they are destined for the sword;And
        his descendants will not have sufficient bread.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Those who survive him will be buried because of the plague,And [their]
        widows will not be able to weep.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Though he heaps up silver like dustAnd piles up clothing like clay,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'He may prepare it, but the just will wear itAnd the innocent will
        divide the silver.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "He builds his house like a spider\u2019s web,Like a (temporary) hut
        which a watchman makes.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'He lies down rich, but never will again;He opens his eyes, and it
        is gone.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Terrors overtake him like a [suddenly rising] flood;A windstorm steals
        him away in the night.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'The east wind lifts him up, and he is gone;It sweeps him out of his
        place.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "For it will hurl [thunderbolts of God\u2019s wrath] at him unsparingly
        and without compassion;He flees in haste from its power.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: People will clap their hands at him [to mock and ridicule him]And
        hiss him out of his place.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Job Tells of Earth\u2019s Treasures"
      title: "Job Tells of Earth\u2019s Treasures"
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CSurely there is a mine for silver,And a place where they
        refine gold.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Iron is taken out of the earth,And copper is smelted from the stone
        ore.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: '  Man puts an end to darkness [by bringing in a light],And to the
        farthest bounds he searches outThe rock buried in gloom and deep shadow.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'He breaks open (mine) shafts far away from where people live,[In
        places] forgotten by the [human] foot;They dangle [in the mines] and hang
        away from men.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: '[As for] the earth, out of it comes food,But underneath [its surface,
        down deep] it is turned over as fire.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Its stones are the bed of sapphires;It holds dust of gold.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "The path [deep within] no bird of prey knows,And the falcon\u2019s
        eye has not caught sight of it.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The proud beasts [and their young] have not walked on it,Nor has
        the fierce lion passed over it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Man puts his hand on [and tears apart] the flinty rock;He overturns
        the mountains at the base [looking for treasure].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'He cuts out channels and passages among the rocks;And his eye sees
        every precious thing.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: The Search for Wisdom Is Harder'
      title: The Search for Wisdom Is Harder
      number: 11
      content: 'Man dams up the streams from flowing [so that they do not trickle
        into the mine],And what is hidden he brings out to the light.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CBut where can wisdom be found?And where is the place of understanding?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Man does not know the value of it;Nor is it found in the land of
        the living.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "The deep says, \u2018It is not in me\u2019;And the sea says, \u2018It
        is not with me.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'It cannot be obtained for pure gold,Nor can silver be weighed as
        its price.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'It cannot be valued in [terms of] the gold of Ophir,In the precious
        onyx or beryl, or the sapphire.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Gold and glass cannot equal wisdom,Nor can it be exchanged for articles
        of fine gold.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'No mention of coral and crystal can be made;For the possession of
        wisdom is even above [that of] rubies or pearls.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'The topaz of Ethiopia cannot compare with it,Nor can it be valued
        in pure gold.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'From where then does wisdom come?And where is the place of understanding?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'It is hidden from the eyes of all the livingAnd concealed from the
        birds of the heavens.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Abaddon (the place of destruction) and Death say,\u2018We have [only]
        heard a report of it with our ears.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "\u201CGod understands the way [to wisdom]And He knows its place [for
        wisdom is with God alone].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'For He looks to the ends of the earthAnd sees everything under the
        heavens.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'When He gave weight and pressure to the windAnd allotted the waters
        by measure,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'When He made a limit for the rainAnd a way for the thunderbolt,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Then He saw wisdom and declared it;He established it and searched
        it out.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "But to man He said, \u2018Behold, the reverential and worshipful
        fear of the Lord\u2014that is wisdom;And to depart from evil is understanding.\u2019\u2009\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Job\u2019s Past Was Glorious"
      title: "Job\u2019s Past Was Glorious"
      number: 1
      content: '  And Job again took up his discussion and said,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201COh, that I were as in the months of old,As in the days when
        God watched over me,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'When His lamp shone upon my head  And by His light I walked through
        darkness;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'As I was in the prime of my days,When the friendship and counsel
        of God were over my tent,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'When the Almighty was still with meAnd my boys were around me,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'When my steps [through rich pastures] were washed with butter and
        cream [from my livestock],And the rock poured out for me streams of oil [from
        my olive groves].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'When I went out to the gate of the city,When I took my seat [as a
        city father] in the square,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The young men saw me and hid themselves,The aged arose and stood
        [respectfully];  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The princes stopped talkingAnd put their hands on their mouths;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The voices of the nobles were hushed,And their tongues stuck to the
        roof of their mouths.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'For when an ear heard [my name mentioned], it called me happy and
        fortunate;And when an eye saw [me], it testified for me [approvingly],  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Because I rescued the poor who cried for help,And the orphan who
        had no helper.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "The blessing of him who was about to perish came upon me,And I made
        the widow\u2019s heart sing for joy.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'I put on righteousness, and it clothed me;My justice was like a robe
        and a turban!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'I was eyes to the blindAnd I was feet to the lame.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'I was a father to the needy;I investigated the case I did not know
        [and assured justice].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And I smashed the jaws of the wickedAnd snatched the prey from his
        teeth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then I said, \u2018I shall die in my nest,And I shall multiply my
        days as the sand.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'My root is spread out and open to the waters,And the dew lies all
        night upon my branch.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "My glory and honor are fresh in me [being constantly renewed],And
        my bow gains [ever] new strength in my hand.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CThey listened to me and waitedAnd kept silent for my counsel.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'After I spoke, they did not speak again,And my speech dropped upon
        them [like a refreshing shower].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'They waited for me [and for my words] as for the rain,And they opened
        their mouths as for the spring rain.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'I smiled at them when they did not believe,And they did not diminish
        the light of my face.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: I chose a way for them and sat as chief,And dwelt as a king among
        his soldiers,As one who comforts mourners.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Job\u2019s Present State Is Humiliating"
      title: "Job\u2019s Present State Is Humiliating"
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CBut now those younger than I mock and laugh at me,Whose fathers
        I refused to put with the sheepdogs of my flock.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Indeed, how could the strength of their hands profit me?Vigor had
        perished from them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'They are gaunt with want and famine;They gnaw the dry and barren
        ground by night in [the gloom of] waste and desolation.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'They pluck [and eat] saltwort (mallows) among the bushes,And their
        food is the root of the broom shrub.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'They are driven from the community;They shout after them as after
        a thief.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'They must dwell on the slopes of wadis  And in holes in the ground
        and in rocks.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Among the bushes they cry out [like wild animals];Beneath the prickly
        scrub they gather and huddle together.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: '  They are the sons of [worthless and nameless] fools,They have been
        driven out of the land.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CAnd now I have become [the subject of] their taunting;Yes,
        I am a byword and a laughingstock to them.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'They hate me, they stand aloof from me,And do not refrain from spitting
        in my face.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'For God has loosed His bowstring [attacking me] and [He has] afflicted
        and humbled me;They have cast off the bridle [of restraint] before me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'On my right the [rabble] brood rises;They push my feet away, and
        they build up their ways of destruction against me [like an advancing army].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'They break up and clutter my path [upsetting my plans],They profit
        from my destruction;No one restrains them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'As through a wide breach they come,Amid the crash [of falling walls]
        they roll on [over me].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Terrors are turned upon me;They chase away my honor and reputation
        like the wind,And my prosperity has passed away like a cloud.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CAnd now my soul is poured out within me;The days of affliction
        have seized me.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'My bones are pierced [with aching] in the night season,And the pains
        that gnaw me take no rest.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'By the great force [of my disease] my garment (skin) is disfigured
        and blemished;It binds about me [choking me] like the collar of my coat.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'God has cast me into the mire [a swampland of crisis],And I have
        become [worthless] like dust and ashes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'I cry to You for help, [Lord,] but You do not answer me;I stand up,
        but You [only] gaze [indifferently] at me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'You have become harsh and cruel to me;With the might of Your hand
        You [keep me alive only to] persecute me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'You lift me up on the wind and cause me to ride [upon it];And You
        toss me about in the tempest and dissolve me in the storm.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'For I know that You will bring me to deathAnd to the house of meeting
        [appointed] for all the living.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u201CHowever, does not one falling in a heap of ruins stretch out
        his hand?Or in his disaster [will he not] therefore cry out for help?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Did I not weep for one whose life was hard and filled with trouble?Was
        not my heart grieved for the needy?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'When I expected good, then came evil [to me];And when I waited for
        light, then came darkness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'I am seething within and my heart is troubled and cannot rest;Days
        of affliction come to meet me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'I go about mourning without comfort [my skin blackened by disease,
        not by the heat of the sun];I stand up in the assembly and cry out for help.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'I am a brother to [howling] jackals,And a companion to ostriches
        [which scream dismally].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'My skin falls from me in blackened flakes,And my bones are burned
        with fever.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: Therefore my lyre (harp) is used for [the sound of] mourning,And my
        flute for the [sound of the] voices of those who weep.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Job Asserts His Integrity'
      title: Job Asserts His Integrity
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CI have made a covenant (agreement) with my eyes;How then
        could I gaze [lustfully] at a virgin?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'For what is the portion I would have from God above,And what heritage
        from the Almighty on high?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Does not tragedy fall [justly] on the unjustAnd disaster to those
        who work wickedness?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Does not God see my waysAnd count all my steps?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CIf I have walked with falsehood,Or if my foot has chased after
        deceit,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Oh, let Him weigh me with accurate scales,And let God know my integrity.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'If my step has turned away from the way [of God],Or if my heart has
        [covetously] followed my eyes,Or if any spot [of guilt] has stained my hands,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Then let me plant and [let] another eat [from the results of my labor],And
        let my crops be uprooted and ruined.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CIf my heart has been enticed and I was made a fool by a woman,Or
        if I have [covetously] lurked at my neighbor\u2019s door [until his departure],  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Let my wife grind [meal, like a bond slave] for another [man],And
        let others kneel down over her.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'For adultery is a heinous and lustful crime;Moreover, it would be
        a sin punishable by the judges.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "For it is a fire which consumes to Abaddon (destruction, ruin, final
        torment);And [illicit passion] would burn and rage and uproot all my [life\u2019s]
        increase [destroying everything].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CIf I have despised and rejected the claim of my male or female
        servantsWhen they filed a complaint against me,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'What then could I do when God arises [to judge me]?When He calls
        me to account, what will I answer Him?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Did not He who made me in the womb make my servant,And did not the
        same One fashion us both in the womb?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CIf I have withheld from the poor what they desired,Or have
        caused the eyes of the widow to look in vain [for relief],  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Or have eaten my morsel [of food] alone,And did not share it with
        the orphan  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "(But from my youth the orphan grew up with me as with a father,And
        from my mother\u2019s womb I have been the widow\u2019s guide),  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'If I have seen anyone perish for lack of clothing,Or any poor person
        without covering,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'If his loins have not thanked and blessed me [for clothing them],And
        if he was not warmed with the fleece of my sheep,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'If I have lifted my hand against the orphan,Because I saw [that the
        judges would be] my help at the [council] gate,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Then let my shoulder fall away from its socket,And my arm be broken
        off at the elbow.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'For tragedy from God is a terror to me,And because of His majesty
        and exaltation I can do nothing [nor endure facing Him].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u201CIf I have put my trust and confidence in gold,Or have declared
        fine gold my hope and assurance,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'If I gloated and rejoiced because my wealth was great,And because
        my [powerful] hand [alone] had obtained so much,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'If I beheld the sun [as an object of worship] when it shoneOr the
        moon going in its splendor,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And my heart became secretly enticed [by them],And my hand threw
        a kiss from my mouth [in respect to them],  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'This also would have been [a heinous] sin calling for judgment,For
        I would have denied God above.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "\u201CHave I rejoiced at the destruction of the enemy [who hated
        me],Or exulted [in malicious triumph] when evil overtook him?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'No, I have not allowed my mouth to sinBy cursing my enemy and asking
        for his life.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "I assure you, the men of my tent have said,\u2018Who can find one
        [in need] who has not been satisfied with his meat\u2019?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'The stranger has not lodged in the street,Because I have opened my
        door to the traveler.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Have I concealed my transgressions like Adam or like other men,By
        hiding my wickedness in my bosom,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Because I feared the great multitude,And the contempt of families
        terrified me,So that I kept silence and did not acknowledge my sin and did
        not go out of the door?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'Oh, that I had one to listen to me!Look, here is my signature (mark);Let
        the Almighty answer me!Let my adversary write out His indictment [and put
        His vague accusations in tangible form].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Surely I would [proudly] bear it on my shoulder,And bind the scroll
        around my head like a crown.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'I would count out to Him the number of my steps [with every detail
        of my life],Approaching His presence as if I were a prince.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "\u201CFor if my land has cried out against me,And its furrows weep
        together;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'If I have eaten its fruits without paying for them,Or have caused
        its [rightful] owners to lose their lives,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "Let thorns grow instead of wheat,And stinkweed and cockleburs instead
        of barley.\u201DSo the words of Job [with his friends] are finished."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Elihu Rebukes Job'
      title: Elihu Rebukes Job
      number: 1
      content: '  So these three men ceased answering Job, because he was righteous
        in his own eyes [and could not be persuaded otherwise by them]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "But Elihu the son of Barachel the Buzite, of the family of Ram, became
        indignant. His indignation was kindled and burned and he became upset with
        Job because he justified himself rather than God [and even expressed doubts
        about God\u2019s character]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Elihu\u2019s anger burned against Job\u2019s three friends because
        they had found no answer [and were unable to determine Job\u2019s error],
        and yet they had condemned Job and declared him to be in the wrong [and responsible
        for his own afflictions]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Now Elihu had waited to speak to Job because the others were years
        older than he. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And when Elihu saw that there was no answer in the mouths of these
        three men, he burned with anger.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then Elihu the son of Barachel the Buzite said,\u201CI am young,
        and you are aged;For that reason I was anxious and dared not tell you what
        I think.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'I thought age should speak,And a multitude of years should teach
        wisdom.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'But there is [a vital force and] a spirit [of intelligence] in man,And
        the breath of the Almighty gives them understanding.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Those [who are] abundant in years may not [always] be wise,Nor may
        the elders [always] understand justice.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Therefore I say, \u2018Listen to me;I also will give you my opinion
        [about Job\u2019s situation] and tell you plainly what I think.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CYou see, I waited for your words,I listened to your [wise]
        reasons,While you pondered and searched out what to say.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'I even paid close attention to [what] you [said],Indeed, not one
        of you convinced Job [nor could you refute him],Not one of you supplied [satisfactory]
        answers to his words.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Beware if you say,\u2018We have found wisdom;God thrusts Job down
        [justly], not man [for God alone is dealing with him].\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Now Job has not directed his words against me [therefore I have no
        reason to be offended],Nor will I answer him with arguments like yours. [I
        speak for truth, not for revenge.]  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CThey (Job\u2019s friends) are dismayed and embarrassed, they
        no longer answer;The words have moved away and failed them,\u201D [says Elihu].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CAnd shall I wait, because they say nothing,But stand still
        and say no more?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'I too will give my share of answers;I too will express my opinion
        and share my knowledge.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'For I am full of words;The spirit within me constrains me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'My belly is like unvented wine;Like new wineskins it is about to
        burst.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'I must speak so that I may get relief;I will open my lips and answer.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'I will not [I warn you] be partial to any man [that is, let my respect
        for you mitigate what I say];Nor flatter any man.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: For I do not know how to flatter, [in an appropriate way, and I fear
        that],My Maker would soon take me away.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Elihu Claims to Speak for God'
      title: Elihu Claims to Speak for God
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CHowever, Job, please listen to my words,And pay attention
        to everything I say.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Behold, I have opened my mouth [to begin my speech];My tongue in
        my mouth is going to speak.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'My words will express the uprightness of my heart,And my lips will
        speak what they know with utter sincerity.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The Spirit of God has made me,And the breath of the Almighty gives
        me life [which inspires me].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Answer me, if you can;Set yourselves before me, take your stand.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Behold, I belong to God like you;I too was formed out of the clay.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Behold, I will not make you afraid or terrified of me [for I am only
        mortal and not God],Nor should any pressure from me weigh heavily upon you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CSurely you have spoken in my hearing,And I have heard the sound
        of your words, saying:  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u2018I am pure, without transgression;I am innocent and there is
        no guilt in me.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Behold, God finds pretexts against me;He counts me as His enemy.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "He puts my feet in the stocks [to hinder and humiliate me];He [suspiciously]
        watches all my paths,\u2019 [you say].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Look, let me answer you, in this you are not right or just;For God
        is greater and far superior to man.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CWhy do you complain against Him?That He does not answer [you
        with] all His doings.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'For God speaks once,And even twice, yet no one notices it [including
        you, Job].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "In a dream, a vision of the night [one may hear God\u2019s voice],When
        deep sleep falls on menWhile slumbering upon the bed,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Then He opens the ears of menAnd seals their instruction,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'That He may turn man aside from his conduct,And keep him from pride;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'He holds back his soul from the pit [of destruction],And his life
        from passing over into Sheol (the nether world, the place of the dead).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CMan is also disciplined with pain on his bed,And with unceasing
        complaint in his bones,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'So that his life makes him loathe food,And his soul [loathe] even
        his favorite dishes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'His flesh is so wasted away that it cannot be seen,And his bones
        which were not seen now stick out.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Then his soul draws near to the pit [of destruction],And his life
        to those who bring death (the destroyers).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "\u201CIf there is an angel as a mediator for him,One out of a thousand,To
        explain to a man what is right for him [that is, how to be in right standing
        with God],  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Then the angel is gracious to him, and says,\u2018Spare him from
        going down to the pit [of destruction];I have found a ransom [a consideration,
        or reason for redemption, an atonement]!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Let his flesh be restored and become fresher than in youth;Let him
        return to the days of his youthful strength.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "He will pray to God, and He shall be favorable to him,So that he
        looks at His face with joy;For God restores to man His righteousness [that
        is, his right standing with God\u2014with its joys].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "He sings out to other men,\u2018I have sinned and perverted that
        which was right,And it was not proper for me!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "God has redeemed my life from going to the pit [of destruction],And
        my life shall see the light.\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "[Elihu comments,] \u201CBehold, God does all these things  twice,
        yes, three times, with a man,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'To bring his life back from the pit [of destruction],That he may
        be enlightened with the light of the living.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Pay attention, Job, listen to me;Keep silent, and I will speak.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'If you have anything to say, answer me;Speak, for I desire to justify
        you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "If not [and you have nothing to say], listen to me;Keep silent, and
        I will teach you wisdom.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Elihu Vindicates God\u2019s Justice"
      title: "Elihu Vindicates God\u2019s Justice"
      number: 1
      content: '  Elihu continued his discourse and said,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CHear my words, you wise men,And listen to me, you who have
        [so much] knowledge.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For the ear puts words to the testAs the palate tastes food.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Let us choose for ourselves that which is right;Let us know among
        ourselves what is good.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "For Job has said, \u2018I am righteous [and innocent],But God has
        taken away my right;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Although I am right, I am accounted a liar.My wound is incurable,
        though I am without transgression.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'What man is like Job,Who drinks up derision like water,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Who goes in company with those who do evilAnd walks with wicked men?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "For he has said, \u2018It profits a man nothingWhen he takes delight
        and is pleased with God and obeys Him.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CTherefore hear me, you men of understanding.Far be it from
        God that He would do wickedness,And from the Almighty to do wrong.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'For God pays a man according to his work,And He will make every man
        find [appropriate] compensation according to his way.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Surely God will not act wickedly,Nor will the Almighty pervert justice.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Who put God in charge over the earth?And who has laid on Him the
        whole world?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'If God should determine to do so,If He should gather to Himself [that
        is, withdraw from man] His [life-giving] spirit and His breath,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'All flesh would perish together,And man would return to dust.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CIf you now have understanding, hear this;Listen to the sound
        of my words.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Shall one who hates justice [and is an enemy of right] govern?And
        will you condemn Him who is just and mighty?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "God who says to a king, \u2018You are worthless and vile,\u2019Or
        to princes and nobles, \u2018You are wicked and evil\u2019?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Who is not partial to princes,Nor does He regard the rich above the
        poor,For they all are the work of His hands.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'In a moment they die, even at midnightThe people are shaken and pass
        away,And the powerful are taken away without a [human] hand.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CFor God\u2019s eyes are on the ways of a man,And He sees all
        his steps.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'There is no darkness nor deep shadowWhere the evildoers may hide
        themselves.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'For He sets no appointed time for a man,That he should appear before
        Him in judgment.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'He breaks mighty men without inquiry,And sets others in their place.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Therefore He knows of their works,And He overthrows them in the night,So
        that they are crushed and destroyed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'He strikes them like the wickedIn a public place,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Because they turned aside from following HimAnd would not consider
        or show regard for any of His ways,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'So that they caused the cry of the poor to come to Him,And He heard
        the cry of the afflicted.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "When He keeps quiet, who then can condemn?When He hides His face
        [withdrawing His favor and help], who then can behold Him [and make supplication
        to Him],Whether it be a nation or a man by himself?\u2014  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'So that godless men would not ruleNor be snares for the people.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "\u201CFor has anyone said to God,\u2018I have endured my chastisement;I
        will not offend anymore;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Teach me what I do not see [in regard to how I have sinned];If I
        have done wrong (injustice, unrighteousness),I will not do it again\u2019?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "Shall God\u2019s retribution [for your sins] be on your terms, because
        you refuse to accept it?For you must do the choosing, and not I;Therefore
        say what you [truthfully] know.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Men of understanding will tell me,Indeed, every wise man who hears
        me [will agree],  '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "\u2018Job speaks without knowledge,And his words are without wisdom
        and insight.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Job ought to be tried to the limitBecause he answers like wicked
        men!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "For he adds rebellion [in his unsubmissive, defiant attitude toward
        God] to his [unacknowledged] sin;He claps his hands among us [in open mockery
        and contempt of God],And he multiplies his words [of accusation] against
        God.\u2019\u2009\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Elihu Sharply Reproves Job'
      title: Elihu Sharply Reproves Job
      number: 1
      content: '  Elihu continued speaking [to Job] and said,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CDo you think this is according to [your] justice?Do you say,
        \u2018My righteousness is more than God\u2019s\u2019?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "For you say, \u2018What advantage have you [by living a righteous
        life]?What profit will I have, more [by being righteous] than if I had sinned?\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'I will answer you,And your companions with you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Look to the heavens and see;And behold the skies which are [much]
        higher than you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'If you have sinned, what do you accomplish against Him?And if your
        transgressions are multiplied, what have you done to Him?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'If you are righteous, what do you give God,Or what does He receive
        from your hand?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Your wickedness affects only a man such as you,And your righteousness
        affects only  a son of man [but it cannot affect God, who is sovereign].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CBecause of the multitudes of oppressions the people cry out;They
        cry for help because of the [violent] arm of the mighty.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "But no one says, \u2018Where is God my Maker,Who gives songs [of
        rejoicing] in the night,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Who teaches us more than the beasts of the earthAnd makes us wiser
        than the birds of the heavens?\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The people cry out, but He does not answerBecause of the pride of
        evil men.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Surely God will not listen to an empty cry [which lacks trust],Nor
        will the Almighty regard it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Even though you say that you do not see Him [when missing His righteous
        judgment on earth],Yet your case is before Him, and you must wait for Him!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And now, because He has not [quickly] punished in His anger,Nor has
        He acknowledged transgression and arrogance well [and seems unaware of the
        wrong of which a person is guilty],  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Job uselessly opens his mouthAnd multiplies words without knowledge
        [drawing the worthless conclusion that the righteous have no more advantage
        than the wicked].\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Elihu Speaks of God\u2019s Dealings with Men"
      title: "Elihu Speaks of God\u2019s Dealings with Men"
      number: 1
      content: '  Elihu continued and said,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CBear with me a little longer, and I will show you,That there
        is yet more to say on God\u2019s behalf.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'I will bring my knowledge from afar,And will ascribe righteousness
        to my Maker.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'For truly my words are not false;He who is perfect in knowledge is
        with you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Behold, God is mighty, and yet does not despise anyone [nor regard
        any as trivial];  He is mighty in the strength and power of understanding.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'He does not prolong the life of the wicked,But gives the afflicted
        their justice.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'He does not withdraw His eyes from the righteous [those in right
        standing with Him];But with kings upon the throneHe has seated them forever,
        and they are exalted.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And if they are bound in bonds [of adversity],And held by cords of
        affliction,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then He declares to them [the true character of] their deedsAnd their
        transgressions, that they have acted arrogantly [with presumption and notions
        of self-sufficiency].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'He opens their ears to instruction and discipline,And commands that
        they return from evil.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'If they hear and serve Him,They will end their days in prosperityAnd
        their years in pleasantness and joy.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "But if they do not hear and obey, they will die by the sword [of
        God\u2019s destructive judgments]And they will die [in ignorance] without
        [true] knowledge.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'But the godless in heart store up anger [at the divine discipline];They
        do not cry [to Him] for help when He binds them [with cords of affliction].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'They die in youth,And their life ends among the cult prostitutes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'He rescues the afflicted in their affliction,And opens their ears
        [so that they pay attention to His voice] in times of oppression.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Then indeed, He enticed you from the mouth of distress and confinement,Into
        a broad place where there is no constraint or distress;And that which was
        set on your table was full of fatness (rich food).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CBut you [Job] were full of judgment on the wicked,Judgment
        and justice take hold of you.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Do not let wrath entice you into scoffing;And do not let the greatness
        and the extent of the ransom turn you aside.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Will your wealth [be sufficient to] keep you from [the confinement
        of] distress,Or will all the force of your strength do it?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Do not long for the night,When people vanish from their places.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Take heed and be careful, do not turn to wickedness,For you have
        chosen this [the vice of complaining against God] rather than [learning from]
        affliction.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Behold, God is exalted in His power;Who is a ruler or a teacher like
        Him?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Who has appointed God His way,And who can say [to Him], \u2018You
        have done wrong\u2019?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u201CRemember that you should magnify God\u2019s work,Of which men
        have sung.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "All men have seen God\u2019s work;Man looks at it from a distance.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Behold, God is exalted, and we do not know Him;The number of His
        years is unsearchable.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'For He draws up the drops of water,They distill rain from the mist,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Which the clouds pour down,They drop abundantly upon mankind.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "\u201CCan anyone understand the spreading of the cloudsOr the thundering
        of His pavilion?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Behold, He spreads His lightning around Him [against the dark clouds],And
        He covers the depths of the sea.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'For by these [mighty acts] He judges the peoples;He gives food in
        abundance.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'He covers His hands with the lightning,And commands it to strike
        the mark.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: His thundering voice declares [awesomely] His presence;The cattle
        also are told of His coming storm.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Elihu Says God has Authority over the Storm'
      title: Elihu Says God has Authority over the Storm
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CIndeed, at His thundering my heart tremblesAnd leaps out
        of its place.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Listen carefully to the thunder of His voice,And the rumbling that
        goes out of His mouth!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'He lets it loose under the whole heaven,And His lightning to the
        ends of the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'After it, His voice roars;He thunders with the voice of His majesty,And
        He does not restrain His lightning [against His adversaries] when His voice
        is heard.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'God thunders marvelously with His voice;He does great things which
        we cannot comprehend.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "For He says to the snow, \u2018Fall on the earth\u2019;And [He speaks]
        to the showers and to the downpour [of His mighty rains], \u2018Be strong.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'God seals (brings to a standstill, stops) [by severe weather] the
        hand of every man,That all men [whom He has made] may know His work [that
        is, His sovereign power and their subjection to it].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Then the beast goes into its lairAnd remains in its hiding place.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Out of its chamber comes the storm,And cold from the north wind.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Ice is made by the breath of God,And the expanse of the waters is
        frozen.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'He loads the thick cloud with moisture;He disperses the cloud of
        His lightning.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Its direction is turned around by His guidance,That it may do whatever
        He commands itOn the face of the inhabited earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Whether [it be] for correction, or for His earth [generally]Or for
        [His] mercy and lovingkindness, He causes it to happen.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CListen to this, Job;Stand still and consider the wonders of
        God.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Do you know how God establishes and commands them,And makes the lightning
        of His [storm] cloud shine?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Do you know about the layers of thick clouds [and how they are balanced
        and poised in the heavens],The wonderful works of Him who is perfect in knowledge,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'You whose garments are hot,When He quiets the earth [in sultry summer]
        with the [oppressive] south wind?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Can you, with Him, spread out the sky,Strong as a molten mirror?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Tell us [Job] what words [of man] shall we say to such a Being;We
        cannot state our case because of darkness [that is, our ignorance in the
        presence of the unsearchable God].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'So shall it be told Him that I wish to speak?Or should a man say
        that he would be swallowed up [and destroyed by God]?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CNow people cannot look at the light when it is bright in the
        skies [without being blinded],When the wind has passed and cleared them.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Out of the north comes golden splendor [and people can hardly look
        on it];Around God is awesome splendor and majesty [far too glorious for man\u2019s
        eyes].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "The Almighty\u2014we cannot find Him;He is exalted in powerAnd He
        will not do violence to [nor disregard] justice and abundant righteousness.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Men therefore fear Him;He does not regard nor respect any who are
        wise in heart [in their own understanding and conceit].\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: God Speaks Now to Job'
      title: God Speaks Now to Job
      number: 1
      content: '  Then the Lord answered Job out of the whirlwind and said,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CWho is this that darkens counsel [questioning my authority
        and wisdom]By words without knowledge?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Now gird up your loins like a man,And I will ask you, and you instruct
        Me!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Where were you when I laid the foundation of the earth?Tell Me, if
        you know and have understanding.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Who determined the measurements [of the earth], if you know?Or who
        stretched the [measuring] line on it?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'On what were its foundations fastened?Or who laid its cornerstone,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'When the morning stars sang togetherAnd all the sons of God (angels)
        shouted for joy?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201COr who enclosed the sea with doorsWhen it burst forth and went
        out of the womb;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'When I made the clouds its garmentAnd thick darkness its swaddling
        band,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And marked for it My [appointed] boundaryAnd set bars and doors [defining
        the shorelines],  '
      comments: []
    - name: "11: God\u2019s Mighty Power"
      title: "God\u2019s Mighty Power"
      number: 11
      content: "And said, \u2018This far you shall come, but no farther;And here
        your proud waves shall stop\u2019?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CSince your days began, have you ever commanded the morning,And
        caused the dawn to know its place,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So that light may take hold of the corners of the earthAnd shake
        the wickedness out of it?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'The earth is changed like clay into which a seal is pressed;And the
        things [of the earth] stand out like a [multi-colored] garment.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Their light is withheld from the wicked,And the uplifted arm is broken.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CHave you entered and explored the springs of the seaOr [have
        you] walked in the recesses of the deep?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Have the gates of death been revealed to you,Or have you seen the
        gates of deep darkness?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Have you understood the expanse of the earth?Tell Me, if you know
        all this.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CWhere is the way where light dwells?And as for darkness, where
        is its place,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'That you may take it to its territoryAnd that you may know the paths
        to its house?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'You [must] know, since you were born then,And because you are so
        extremely old!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Have you entered the storehouses of the snow,Or have you seen the
        storehouses of the hail,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Which I have reserved for the time of trouble,For the day of battle
        and war?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Where is the way that the light is distributed,Or the east wind scattered
        over the earth?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CWho has prepared a channel for the torrents of rain and for
        the flood,Or a path for the thunderbolt,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'To bring rain on the uninhabited land,And on the desert where no
        man lives,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'To satisfy the barren and desolate groundAnd to make the seeds of
        grass to sprout?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Has the rain a father?Or who has begotten the drops of dew?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Out of whose womb has come the ice?And the frost of heaven, who has
        given it birth?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Water becomes like stone [and hides itself],And the surface of the
        deep is frozen and imprisoned.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "\u201CCan you bind the chains of [the cluster of stars called] Pleiades,Or
        loose the cords of [the constellation] Orion?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Can you lead forth a constellation in its season,And guide [the stars
        of] the Bear with her sons?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Do you know the ordinances of the heavens,Or [can you] establish
        their rule over the earth?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "\u201CCan you lift up your voice to the clouds,So that an abundance
        of water will cover you?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "Can you send forth lightnings that they may goAnd say to you, \u2018Here
        we are\u2019?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Who has put wisdom in the innermost being [of man, or in the layers
        of clouds]Or given understanding to the mind [of man, or to the heavenly
        display]?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'Who can count the clouds by [earthly] wisdom,Or pour out the water
        jars of the heavens,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'When the dust hardens into a massAnd the clods stick together [because
        of the heat]?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "\u201CCan you [Job] hunt the prey for the lion,Or satisfy the appetite
        of the young lions  "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'When they crouch in their densAnd lie in wait in their lair?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: Who provides prey for the ravenWhen its young cry to GodAnd wander
        about without food?
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: God Speaks of Nature and Its Beings'
      title: God Speaks of Nature and Its Beings
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CDo you know the time when the wild goats of the rock give
        birth [to their young]?Do you observe the calving of the deer?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Can you count the months that they carry offspring,Or do you know
        the time when they give birth?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'They kneel down, they bring forth their young,They cast out their
        labor pains.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Their young ones become strong, they grow up in the open field;They
        leave and do not return to them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CWho sent out the wild donkey free [from dependence on man]?And
        who has loosed the bonds of the wild donkey [to survive in the wild],  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'To whom I gave the wilderness as his homeAnd the salt land as his
        dwelling place?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'He scorns the tumult of the city,And does not hear the shouting of
        the taskmaster.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'He explores the mountains as his pastureAnd searches after every
        green thing.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Will the wild ox be willing to serve you,Or remain beside your manger
        at night?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Can you bind the wild ox with a harness [to the plow] in the furrow?Or
        will he plow the valleys for you?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Will you trust him because his strength is greatAnd leave your labor
        to him?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Will you have faith and depend on him to return your grainAnd gather
        it from your threshing floor?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CThe [flightless] wings of the ostrich wave joyously;With the
        pinion (shackles, fetters) and plumage of love,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'For she leaves her eggs on the groundAnd warms them in the dust,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Forgetting that a foot may crush them,Or that the wild beast may
        trample them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'She treats her young cruelly, as if they were not hers;Though her
        labor is in vain because she is unconcerned [for the safety of her brood],  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'For God has made her forget wisdom,And has not given her a share
        of understanding.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Yet when she lifts herself on high,[So swift is she that] she laughs
        at the horse and his rider.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CHave you given the horse his might?Have you clothed his neck
        with quivering and a shaking mane?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Have you [Job] made him leap like a locust?The majesty of his snorting
        [nostrils] is terrible.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'He paws in the valley and rejoices in his strength;He goes out to
        meet the weapons [of armed men].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'He laughs at fear and is not dismayed;And [in battle] he does not
        turn back from the sword.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'The quiver rattles against him,[As do] the flashing spear and the
        lance [of his rider].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'With fierceness and rage he races to devour the ground,And he does
        not stand still at the sound of the [war] trumpet.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "As often as the trumpet sounds he says, \u2018Aha!\u2019And he smells
        the battle from far away,And senses the thunder of the captains and the war
        cry.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "\u201CIs it by your understanding that the hawk soars,Stretching
        his wings toward the south [as winter approaches]?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Is it at your command that the eagle mounts upAnd makes his nest
        on high [in an inaccessible place]?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'On the cliff he dwells and remains [securely],Upon the point of the
        rock and the inaccessible stronghold.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'From there he spies out the prey;His eyes see it from far away.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "His young ones suck up blood;And where the slain are, there is he.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Job: What Can I Say?'
      title: 'Job: What Can I Say?'
      number: 1
      content: '  Then the Lord said to Job,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CWill the faultfinder contend with the Almighty?Let him who
        disputes with God answer it.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then Job replied to the Lord and said,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CBehold, I am of little importance and contemptible; what can
        I reply to You?I lay my hand on my mouth.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: God Questions Job'
      title: God Questions Job
      number: 5
      content: "I have spoken once, but I will not reply again\u2014Indeed, twice
        [I have answered], and I will add nothing further.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then the Lord answered Job out of the whirlwind, saying,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CNow gird up your loins (prepare yourself) like a man,And I
        will ask you, and you instruct Me.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Will you really annul My judgment and set it aside as void?Will you
        condemn Me [your God] that you may [appear to] be righteous and justified?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Have you an arm like God,And can you thunder with a voice like His?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CAdorn yourself with eminence and dignity [since you question
        the Almighty],And array yourself with honor and majesty.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Pour out the overflowings of your wrath,And look at everyone who
        is proud and make him low.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Look at everyone who is proud, and humble him,And [if you are so
        able] tread down the wicked where they stand.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: '[Crush and] hide them in the dust together;Shut them up in the hidden
        place [the house of death].  '
      comments: []
    - name: "14: God\u2019s Power Shown in Creatures"
      title: "God\u2019s Power Shown in Creatures"
      number: 14
      content: '[If you can do all this, Job, proving your divine power] then I [God]
        will also praise you and acknowledgeThat your own right hand can save you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CBehold now, Behemoth, which I created as well as you;He eats
        grass like an ox.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'See now, his strength is in his loinsAnd his power is in the muscles
        and sinews of his belly.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'He sways his tail like a cedar;The tendons of his thighs are twisted
        and knit together [like a rope].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'His bones are tubes of bronze;His limbs are like bars of iron.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CHe is the first [in magnitude and power] of the works of God;[Only]
        He who made him can bring near His sword [to master him].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Surely the mountains bring him food,And all the wild animals play
        there.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'He lies down under the lotus plants,In the hidden shelter of the
        reeds in the marsh.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'The lotus plants cover him with their shade;The willows of the brook
        surround him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'If a river rages and overflows, he does not tremble;He is confident,
        though the Jordan [River] swells and rushes against his mouth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: Can anyone capture him when he is on watch,Or pierce his nose with
        barbs [to trap him]?
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: God\u2019s Power Shown in Creatures"
      title: "God\u2019s Power Shown in Creatures"
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CCan you draw out Leviathan with a fishhook?Or press down
        his tongue with a cord?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Can you put a rope [made] of rushes into his noseOr pierce his jaw
        through with a hook?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Will he make many supplications to you [begging to be spared]?Or
        will he speak soft words to you [to coax you to treat him kindly]?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Will he make a covenant or an arrangement with you?Will you take
        him for your servant forever?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Will you play with him as with a bird?Or will you bind him [and put
        him on a leash] for your maidens?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Will traders bargain over him?Will they divide him up among the merchants?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Can you fill his skin with harpoons,Or his head with fishing spears?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Lay your hand on him;Remember the battle [with him]; you will not
        do such [an ill-advised thing] again!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "  Behold, his [assailant\u2019s] hope and expectation [of defeating
        Leviathan] is false;Will not one be overwhelmed even at the sight of him?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "No one is so fierce [and foolhardy] that he dares to stir up Leviathan;Who
        then is he who can stand before Me [or dares to contend with Me, the beast\u2019s
        creator]?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Who has first given to Me that I should repay him?Whatever is under
        the whole heaven is Mine. [Who can have a claim against Me who made the unmastered
        beast?]  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CI will not keep silence concerning his limbs,Nor his mighty
        strength, nor his orderly frame.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Who can penetrate or strip off his outer armor?Who can come to his
        jaws with a double bridle?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Who can open the doors (jaws) of his face?Around his [open jaws and]
        teeth there is terror.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'His strong scales are his pride,Bound together as with a tight seal.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'One is so near to anotherThat no air can come between them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'They are joined one to another;They stick together and cannot be
        separated.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'His sneezes flash forth light,And his eyes are like the [reddish]
        eyelids of the dawn.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Out of his mouth go burning torches,And sparks of fire leap out.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Out of his nostrils smoke goes forthAs from a boiling pot and [as
        from] burning rushes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'His breath kindles coals,And a flame goes forth from his mouth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "In Leviathan\u2019s neck resides strength,And dismay and terror dance
        before him.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'The folds of his flesh are joined together,Firm on him and immobile
        [when he moves].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'His heart is as hard as a stone,Indeed, as solid as a lower millstone.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'When he raises himself up, the mighty are afraid;Because of the crashing
        they are bewildered.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'The sword that reaches him cannot avail,Nor [does] the spear, the
        dart, or the javelin.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'He considers iron as straw,Bronze as rotten wood.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'The arrow cannot make him flee;Slingstones are treated as stubble
        by him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Clubs [also] are regarded as stubble;He laughs at the rushing and
        the rattling of the javelin.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'His underparts are like sharp pieces of broken pottery;He moves across
        and spreads out [grooves] like a threshing sledge on the mire (muddy river
        banks).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'He makes the deep water boil like a pot;He makes the sea like a [foaming]
        pot of ointment.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Behind him he makes a shining wake;One would think the deep to be
        gray-haired [with foam].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "Upon earth there is nothing like him\u2014no equal exists,A creature
        made without fear.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "He looks on everything that is high [without terror];He is monarch
        over all the sons of pride. [And now, Job, who are you who does not dare
        to disturb the beast, yet who dares resist Me, the beast\u2019s creator?
        Everything under the heavens is Mine; therefore, who can have a claim against
        God?]\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Job\u2019s Confession"
      title: "Job\u2019s Confession"
      number: 1
      content: '  Then Job answered the Lord and said,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CI know that You can do all things,And that no thought or purpose
        of Yours can be restrained.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "[You said to me] \u2018Who is this that darkens and obscures counsel
        [by words] without knowledge?\u2019Therefore [I now see] I have [rashly]
        uttered that which I did not understand,Things too wonderful for me, which
        I did not know.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u2018Hear, please, and I will speak;I will ask You, and You instruct
        [and answer] me.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'I had heard of You [only] by the hearing of the ear,But now my [spiritual]
        eye sees You.  '
      comments: []
    - name: "6: God Displeased with Job\u2019s Friends"
      title: "God Displeased with Job\u2019s Friends"
      number: 6
      content: "Therefore I retract [my words and hate myself]And I repent in dust
        and ashes.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "It came about that after the Lord had spoken these words to Job,
        that the Lord said to Eliphaz the Temanite, \u201CMy wrath is kindled against
        you and against your two friends, for you have not spoken of Me what is right,
        as My servant Job has. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Now therefore, take for yourselves seven bulls and seven rams, and
        go to My servant Job, and offer up a burnt offering for yourselves, and My
        servant Job will pray for you. For I will accept him [and his prayer] so
        that I may not deal with you according to your folly, because you have not
        spoken of Me the thing that is right, as My servant Job has.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: "9: God Restores Job\u2019s Fortunes"
      title: "God Restores Job\u2019s Fortunes"
      number: 9
      content: "So Eliphaz the Temanite and Bildad the Shuhite and Zophar the Naamathite
        went and did as the Lord told them; and the Lord accepted Job\u2019s prayer.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The Lord restored the fortunes of Job when he prayed for his friends,
        and the Lord gave Job twice as much as he had before. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then all his brothers and sisters and all who had known him before
        came to him, and they ate bread with him in his house; and they consoled
        him and comforted him over all the [distressing] adversities that the Lord
        had brought on him. And each one gave him a piece of money, and each a ring
        of gold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And the Lord blessed the latter days of Job more than his beginning;
        for he had 14,000 sheep, 6,000 camels, 1,000 yoke of oxen, and 1,000 female
        donkeys. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'He had seven sons and three daughters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And he called the name of the first [daughter] Jemimah, and the name
        of the second Keziah, and the name of the third Keren-happuch. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'In all the land there were found no women so fair as the daughters
        of Job; and their father gave them an inheritance among their brothers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'After this, Job lived 140 years, and saw his sons and his grandsons,
        four generations. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: So Job died, an old man and full of days.
      comments: []
